(667, 2, '2015-06-23 06:25:00', '2015-06-23 06:25:00', '<strong><a title="Circular Motion" href="http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Circular-Motion.pdf" target="_blank">Circular Motion Screens</a></strong>\n\nThese Screens are used to segregate various size fractions in coal/ lignite streams. These are also used to reduce load on crushers by removing fraction which is already smaller than required size or to recirculate oversize fractions from crushed product stream back to crushers. Possible application is in Mines before dispatch to power plants. These Screens are available in 1, 2 and 3 decks to get 2, 3 and 4 size fractions respectively. Each size fraction may be requiring different post processing.\n\n<strong><a title="Linear Motion Screen" href="http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Linear-Motion-Screen1.pdf" target="_blank">Linear Motion Screens</a></strong>\n\n<a title="Linear Motion Screen" href="http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Linear-Motion-Screen1.pdf" target="_blank">Linear Motion Screens</a> are used in similar situations as above but where the height is limited by surrounding facilities or screening of small fractions and high throughput is required.\n\n<strong><a title="Roller Screen" href="http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Roller-Screen.pdf" target="_blank">Roller Screens</a></strong>\n\nAs opposed to above two types which are based on bed stratification principle, <a title="Roller Screen" href="http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Roller-Screen.pdf" target="_blank">Roller Screens</a> are based on free fall principle. These are used in screening Run of Mine coal/ lignite when feed stream consists of difficult, sticky, clayey, moist materials and would choke and blind the screen apertures of normal screening machines. It is also good for handling feed material containing larger boulders along with smaller particles\n\n<strong><a title="High Particle Acceleration HPA Screen" href="http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/High-Particle-Acceleration-HPA-Screen.pdf" target="_blank">High Particle Acceleration Screens</a></strong>\n\nAlso known as Flip Flo Screen, these are ideally suited for screening applications for fine grain size materials (3 mm to 10 mm) with high moisture and screening capacities up to 250 metric TPH. The outer frame is agitated by means of eccentric shaft drive. The vibration is passed on to the inner frame via flexible thrust plates.\nScreening mats between the inner and outer frame are clamped and flexed by the two vibrating frames. The relative movement of both screening frames creates a “trampoline effect” in the screen mats to create-\n<ul>\n	<li>High acceleration up to 50g in screen mats.</li>\n	<li>Loosening-up and de-agglomeration of the product.</li>\n</ul>\n<strong>Grizzly Feeders /Vibrating Feeders</strong>\n\nThese Feeders are used to reclaim feed stream from storage bins/ hoppers or as a feeding equipment to crusher &amp; screen where the materials are not easy to handle (wet, clayey or lot of ash content), having size fractions ranging from big lumps to significantly high percentage of wet/moist fines and where scalping is also needed.\n\n<strong>Motorised Trippers</strong>\n\nThese devices are mounted on conveyor belts running on top of long bunkers with several compartments and are used to discharge the material from the conveyor equitably all along the length of the bunker.\n\n<strong>Roll Crushers</strong>\n\n<a title="Single Roll Crusher" href="http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Single-Roll-Crusher.pdf" target="_blank">Single Roll Crushers</a> are used to crush ROM Coal (1000 mm- 1500 mm size) to (-) 200-300 mm size. In Coal Preparation Plants the coal feed is to be further crushed to (-) 25 mm size by using <a title="Double Roll Crusher" href="http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Double-Roll-Crusher.pdf" target="_blank">Toothed Double Roll Crushers</a>. <a title="Smooth Double Roll Crusher" href="http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Smooth-Roll-Crusher.pdf" target="_blank">Smooth Double Roll Crushers</a> can be used for crushing up to (-) 5mm.\n\n<strong><a title="Rotary Braker" href="http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Rotary-Braker.pdf" target="_blank">Rotary Breakers</a></strong>\n\nThese are used to separate hard rock lumps from coal while crushing the ROM size (up to 500 mm) to (125 - 200 mm) in situations where coal’s hardness is significantly lower compared to that of contaminating stones/rocks.\n\n<strong><a title="Ring Granulator" href="http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Ring-Granulator.pdf" target="_blank">Ring Granulators</a></strong>\n\nThese are special purpose crushers for producing (-) 25 mm granular coal from (-) 300 mm feed, and are commonly used in Coal Handling Plants of Thermal Power Stations in all types of Coal Combustion Systems.\n\n<strong><a title="Coal Impactor" href="http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/EK-Series-Impactor.pdf" target="_blank">Coal Impactors</a> (EK Series Impactor)</strong>\n\nEK series Impactors are used for higher capacities and crushing coal up to (-)6 mm product with control of fines. These are very good for FBC type Boiler application. These are also suitable for coal used in Washery and Sponge Iron Plants.\n\n<strong>Conveyor Components</strong>\n\nMSEL product range includes all types of drive and non-drive pulleys and idlers.\n\n<strong>Reciprocating Feeders</strong>\n\nThese are used to reclaim coal from surge bins/ bunkers to feed crushers or conveyors typically up to 1000 tph.\n\n<strong>Vibrating Screen- Feeders</strong>\n\nThese are screens entrusted with two tasks; that of feeding to Crushers and of pre-screening or scalping the feed to crushers. These may be of <a title="Linear Motion Screen" href="http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Linear-Motion-Screen1.pdf" target="_blank">Linear Motion Screen</a> with Geared Exciters or of Twin Eccentric Shaft in Oil Bath type.\n\n<strong><a title="Slurry Pumps" href="http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Slurry-Pumps.pdf" target="_blank">Slurry Pumps</a></strong>\n\nIn coal/ lignite mines and coal/ lignite handling plants these are used for dewatering the sump pits. In coal beneficiation plants these are used in conveying coal slurries from jigs to sieve bends/ dewatering screens or thickeners, flotation equipment and filters.\n\n<strong><a title="Thickener" href="http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Thickener.pdf" target="_blank">Thickeners</a></strong>\n\nThese are used in Coal Beneficiation Circuits to dewater/ thicken coal/ reject slurries for further processing use.\n\n<strong><a title="Flotation Cell" href="http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Flotation-CELL.pdf" target="_blank">Flotation Cells </a></strong>\n\nThese are used to concentrate and separate coal from gangue minerals in some beneficiation circuits for coal.\n\n<strong>Filter Press</strong>\n\nFor the best squeezing of the coal fines or tails, we offer MSEL-Choquenet Filter press.\n\n<strong><a title="Mobile Crushing Screening Plant" href="http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Mobile-Crushing-Screening-Plant.pdf" target="_blank">Skid Mounted Crushing and Screening Plants</a></strong>\n\nThese are semi mobile units to be used when the mine face or pit is continuously shifted and where stationary Coal Crushing Plants would be unsuitable because of long haulage when mine face/pit becomes distant.\n\n<strong><a title="Apron Feeder" href="http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Apron-Feeder.pdf" target="_blank">Apron Feeders</a></strong>\n\nThese are extensively used to reclaim ROM/ Large Size Coal from Dump Hoppers for primary crushing.\n\n<strong>Wagon Tipplers</strong>\n\nIn Coal Handling Plants which are distant from Mines the ROM Coal is brought by rail and unloaded into Hoppers by Wagon Tipplers.\n\n<strong>Paddle Feeders</strong>\n\nThese are used for continuous reclaiming of coal from long length coal hoppers on to conveyors for further processing.\n\n<strong>Bucket Wheel Stacker cum Reclaimers</strong>\n\nThese are used in Coal/ Lignite Handling Plants to create large ground stockpiles of coal/ lignite and also to reclaim from the stockpile.', 'COAL & LIGNITE', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '607-autosave-v1', '', '', '2015-06-23 06:25:00', '2015-06-23 06:25:00', '', 607, 'http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/607-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(668, 2, '2015-01-31 08:36:39', '2015-01-31 08:36:39', '<strong>CM Screens</strong>\r\n\r\nAlso known as Circular Motion Screens, these are used to segregate various size fractions in coal/lignite streams. Sometimes used to reduce load on crushers by removing fraction which is already smaller than required size at other times these are used to recirculate oversize fractions from crushed product stream back to crushers. Possible application is in Mines before despatch to power plants. These Screens are available in 1, 2 and 3 decks to get 2, 3 and 4 size fractions respectively. Each size fraction may be requiring different post processing.\r\n\r\n<strong>LM Screens</strong>\r\n\r\nLinear Motion Screens are used in similar situations as above but where the height is limited by surrounding facilities, for the screening of small and short fractions and required throughput is high.\r\n\r\n<strong>Roller Screens</strong>\r\n\r\nAs opposed to above two types which are based on bed stratification principle, Roller Screens are based on free fall principle. These are used in screening Run of Mine coal/lignite when feed stream consists of difficult sticky clayey moist materials and would choke and blind the screen apertures of normal screening machines.\r\n\r\n<strong>Grizzly Feeders</strong>\r\n\r\nThese Feeders are used to reclaim feed stream from storage bins/ hoppers where the materials are not easy to handle (wet, clayey or lot of ash content), having size fractions ranging from big lumps to significantly high percentage of wet/moist fines and where scalping is also needed.\r\n\r\n<strong>Motorised Trippers</strong>\r\n\r\nThese devices are mounted on conveyor belts running on top of long bunkers with several compartments and are used to discharge the material from the conveyor equitably all along the length of the bunker.\r\n\r\n<strong>Roll Crushers</strong>\r\n\r\nSingle Roll Crushers are used to crush ROM Coal (1500 mm- 1000 mm size) to (-) 300-200 mm size. In Coal Preparation Plants the coal feed is to be further crushed to (-) 25 mm size by using Toothed Double Roll Crushers. Smooth DR Crushers can be used for crushing up to (-) 5mm.\r\n\r\n<strong>Rotary Breakers</strong>\r\n\r\nThese are used to separate hard rock lumps from coal while crushing the ROM (400-300 mm) to (150-200 mm) in situations where coal’s hardness is significantly lower to that of contaminating stones/rocks.\r\n\r\n<strong>Ring Granulators</strong>\r\n\r\nThese are special purpose crushers for producing (-)25 mm granular coal from (-) 250 mm feed, and are commonly used in Coal Handling Plants pf Thermal Power Stations in all types of Coal Combustion systems.\r\n\r\n<strong>Coal Impactors</strong>\r\n\r\nFor higher capacities and crushing to (-) 5mm, impactors/hammer mills are used.\r\n\r\n<strong>Conveyor Components</strong>\r\n\r\nMSEL product range includes all types of drive and non-drive pulleys, and idlers.\r\n\r\n<strong>Reciprocating Feeders</strong>\r\n\r\nThese are used to reclaim coal from surge bins/bunkers to feed crushers or conveyors typically up to 1000 tph.\r\n\r\n<strong>Vibrating Screen- Feeders</strong>\r\n\r\nThese are screens entrusted with two tasks; that of feeding to Crushers and of pre-screening or scalping the feed to crushers. These may be of Linear Motion types with Geared Exciters or of Twin Eccentric Shaft in Oil Bath type.\r\n\r\n<strong>Slurry Pumps</strong>\r\n\r\nIn coal/lignite mines and coal/lignite handling plants these are used for dewatering the sump pits. In coal beneficiation plants these are used in conveying coal slurries from jigs to sieve bends/dewatering screens or thickeners, flotation equipment and filters.\r\n\r\n<strong>Thickeners</strong>\r\n\r\nThese are used in Coal Beneficiation Circuits to dewater/ thicken coal/reject slurries for further processing use.\r\n\r\n<strong>U Flotation Cells</strong>\r\n\r\nThese are used to concentrate and separate coal from gangue minerals in some beneficiation circuits for coal.\r\n\r\n<strong>Filter Press</strong>\r\n\r\nFor the best squeezing of the coal fines or tails we can offer MSEL-Choquenet Filter press.\r\n\r\n<strong>Skid Mounted Crushing and Screening Plants</strong>\r\n\r\nThese are semi mobile units to be used when the mine face or pit is continuously shifted and where stationary Coal Crushing Plants would be unsuitable because of long haulage when mine face/pit becomes distant.\r\n\r\n<strong>Apron Feeders</strong>\r\n\r\nThese are extensively used to reclaim ROM/ Large Size Coal from Dump Hoppers for primary crushing.\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n<strong>Wagon Tipplers</strong>\r\n\r\nIn Coal Handling Plants which are distant from Mines the ROM Coal is brought by rail and unloaded into Hoppers by Wagon Tipplers.\r\n\r\n<strong>Paddle Feeders</strong>\r\n\r\nThese are used for continuous reclaiming of coal from long length coal hoppers on to conveyors for further processing.\r\n\r\n<strong>Bucket Wheel Stacker cum Reclaimers</strong>\r\n\r\nThese are used in Coal/Lignite Handling Plants to create large ground stockpiles of coal/lignite and also to reclaim from the stockpile.', 'COAL AND LIGNITE', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '607-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-31 08:36:39', '2015-01-31 08:36:39', '', 607, 'http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/607-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(574, 1, '2014-11-26 00:03:09', '2014-11-26 00:03:09', 'McNally Sayaji Engineering Limited (MSEL), has been formed by the merger of Product Division of McNally Bharat Engineering Company Limited having factories at Kumardhubi, Asansol and Bangalore with the 60 year old Sayaji Iron &amp; Engineering Co. Ltd. of Baroda. MSEL is one of the country’s leading manufacturers of Crushing, Screening, Grinding, Material Handling &amp; other heavy equipment, serving the core sector industries.\r\n\r\nThe Product range includes Mobile Crushing &amp; Screening Plants, Skid Mounted Crushing Plants, Crushers, Screens, Grinding Mills, Feeders, Scrubbers, Stockyard equipment such as Stacker Reclaimers, Wagon Tipplers, Paddle Feeders. Open cast mining machinery such as Bucket Wheel Excavators, Shiftable Conveyors, Spreaders, Port Cranes. Mineral Processing plants such as Hydrocyclones, Flotation Cells, Thickeners, Slurry Pumps, Pressure Vessels, Heat Exchangers, Rotary Kilns, Driers, Coal Washeries etc. MSEL has recently also ventured into manufacturing critical fabricated equipment for nuclear power industry like Reactor Building Main Airlock doors. The Asansol &amp; Kumardhubi II units have been manufacturing critical equipment for the steel industry as per designs provided by International clients.\r\n\r\nMSEL has four manufacturing units located at Kumardhubi in Jharkand, Asansol in West Bengal, Bangalore &amp; Baroda. The manufacturing units have ISO 9001 - 2008 certification. In addition the Kumardhubi unit is certified for ISO 14001-2004. With Marketing &amp; Branch offices located at Kolkata, Baroda, Kumardhubi, Bangalore, Chennai, Secunderabad, Cochin, Nagpur, Vizag and Vijaywada, MSEL is geared to provide total customer support in any part of the country.\r\n\r\nMSEL has absorbed technology over the years through various strategic alliances and has established a strong R&amp;D and Design &amp; Development team to provide optimum and cost effective solutions to customer needs. The Department of Scientific &amp; Industrial Research (DSIR), a Government of India organization has given recognition to the In-house R&amp;D activities of MSEL.\r\n\r\nMSEL is a subsidiary of McNally Bharat Engineering Co. Ltd., one of the leading Engineering Companies in India having a Group turnover of around US $ 500 Million in 2012-13 and is a publicly listed company on the major stock exchanges of India. MBE has diversified interests in EPC business in Power &amp; Coal, Mining &amp; Metals, Steel, Port &amp; Shipyard, Cement, Oil &amp; Gas, Water and Infrastructure.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<div class="leftcoll"><img src="http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/wp-content/themes/Mbe/images/collage.jpg" alt="" /></div>\r\n<div class="rightcoll"><a class="brochuicon" href="#">Click here for Brochures</a>\r\n<div class="clr"></div>\r\n<a class="videoicon" href="http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/corporate-film/">Click here for Corporate Video</a>\r\n</div>', 'About Us', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '7-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-11-26 00:03:09', '2014-11-26 00:03:09', '', 7, 'http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/7-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
