hese are used in screening Run of Mine coal/ lignite when feed stream consists of difficult, sticky, clayey, moist materials and would choke and blind the screen apertures of normal screening machines. It is also good for handling feed material containing larger boulders along with smaller particles\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"><a style="color: #000000;" title="High Particle Acceleration HPA Screen" href="http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/High-Particle-Acceleration-HPA-Screen.pdf" target="_blank"><strong>High Particle Acceleration Screens</strong></a></span>\r\n\r\nAlso known as Flip Flo Screen, these are ideally suited for screening applications for fine grain size materials (3 mm to 10 mm) with high moisture and screening capacities up to 250 metric TPH. The outer frame is agitated by means of eccentric shaft drive. The vibration is passed on to the inner frame via flexible thrust plates.\r\nScreening mats between the inner and outer frame are clamped and flexed by the two vibrating frames. The relative movement of both screening frames creates a “trampoline effect” in the screen mats to create-\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>High acceleration up to 50g in screen mats.</li>\r\n	<li>Loosening-up and de-agglomeration of the product.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"><strong>Grizzly Feeders /Vibrating Feeders</strong></span>\r\n\r\nThese Feeders are used to reclaim feed stream from storage bins/ hoppers or as a feeding equipment to crusher &amp; screen where the materials are not easy to handle (wet, clayey or lot of ash content), having size fractions ranging from big lumps to significantly high percentage of wet/moist fines and where scalping is also needed.\r\n\r\n<strong>Motorised Trippers</strong>\r\n\r\nThese devices are mounted on conveyor belts running on top of long bunkers with several compartments and are used to discharge the material from the conveyor equitably all along the length of the bunker.\r\n\r\n<strong>Roll Crushers</strong>\r\n\r\n<a title="Single Roll Crusher" href="http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Single-Roll-Crusher.pdf" target="_blank"><span style="color: #000000;">Single Roll Crushers</span></a> are used to crush ROM Coal (1000 mm- 1500 mm size) to (-) 200-300 mm size. In Coal Preparation Plants the coal feed is to be further crushed to (-) 25 mm size by using <a title="Double Roll Crusher" href="http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Double-Roll-Crusher.pdf" target="_blank"><span style="color: #000000;">Toothed Double Roll Crushers</span></a>. <a title="Smooth Double Roll Crusher" href="http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Smooth-Roll-Crusher.pdf" target="_blank"><span style="color: #000000;">Smooth Double Roll Crushers</span></a> can be used for crushing up to (-) 5mm.\r\n\r\n<strong><span style="color: #000000;"><a style="color: #000000;" title="Rotary Braker" href="http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Rotary-Braker.pdf" target="_blank">Rotary Breakers</a></span></strong>\r\n\r\nThese are used to separate hard rock lumps from coal while crushing the ROM size (up to 500 mm) to (125 - 200 mm) in situations where coal’s hardness is significantly lower compared to that of contaminating stones/rocks.\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"><a style="color: #000000;" title="Ring Granulator" href="http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Ring-Granulator.pdf" target="_blank"><strong>Ring Granulators</strong></a></span>\r\n\r\nThese are special purpose crushers for producing (-) 25 mm granular coal from (-) 300 mm feed, and are commonly used in Coal Handling Plants of Thermal Power Stations in all types of Coal Combustion Systems.\r\n\r\n<strong><span style="color: #000000;"><a style="color: #000000;" title="Coal Impactor" href="http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/EK-Series-Impactor.pdf" target="_blank">Coal Impactors</a></span> (EK Series Impactor)</strong>\r\n\r\nEK series Impactors are used for higher capacities and crushing coal up to (-)6 mm product with control of fines. These are very good for FBC type Boiler application. These are also suitable for coal used in Washery and Sponge Iron Plants.\r\n\r\n<strong>Conveyor Components</strong>\r\n\r\nMSEL product range includes all types of drive and non-drive pulleys and idlers.\r\n\r\n<strong><span style="color: #000000;">Reciprocating Feeders</span></strong>\r\n\r\nThese are used to reclaim coal from surge bins/ bunkers to feed crushers or conveyors typically up to 1000 tph.\r\n\r\n<strong>Vibrating Screen- Feeders</strong>\r\n\r\nThese are screens entrusted with two tasks; that of feeding to Crushers and of pre-screening or scalping the feed to crushers. These may be of <span style="color: #000000;"><a style="color: #000000;" title="Linear Motion Screen" href="http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Linear-Motion-Screen1.pdf" target="_blank">Linear Motion Screen</a></span> with Geared Exciters or of Twin Eccentric Shaft in Oil Bath type.\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"><a style="color: #000000;" title="Slurry Pumps" href="http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Slurry-Pumps.pdf" target="_blank"><strong>Slurry Pumps</strong></a></span>\r\n\r\nIn coal/ lignite mines and coal/ lignite handling plants these are used for dewatering the sump pits. In coal beneficiation plants these are used in conveying coal slurries from jigs to sieve bends/ dewatering screens or thickeners, flotation equipment and filters.\r\n\r\n<a title="Thickener" href="http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Thickener.pdf" target="_blank"><span style="color: #000000;"><strong>Thickeners</strong></span></a>\r\n\r\nThese are used in Coal Beneficiation Circuits to dewater/ thicken coal/ reject slurries for further processing use.\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"><a style="color: #000000;" title="Flotation Cell" href="http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Flotation-CELL.pdf" target="_blank"><strong>Flotation Cells</strong> </a></span>\r\n\r\nThese are used to concentrate and separate coal from gangue minerals in some beneficiation circuits for coal.\r\n\r\n<strong>Filter Press</strong>\r\n\r\nFor the best squeezing of the coal fines or tails, we offer MSEL-Choquenet Filter press.\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"><a style="color: #000000;" title="Mobile Crushing Screening Plant" href="http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Mobile-Crushing-Screening-Plant.pdf" target="_blank"><strong>Skid Mounted Crushing and Screening Plants</strong></a></span>\r\n\r\nThese are semi mobile units to be used when the mine face or pit is continuously shifted and where stationary Coal Crushing Plants would be unsuitable because of long haulage when mine face/pit becomes distant.\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"><a style="color: #000000;" title="Apron Feeder" href="http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Apron-Feeder.pdf" target="_blank"><strong>Apron Feeders</strong></a></span>\r\n\r\nThese are extensively used to reclaim ROM/ Large Size Coal from Dump Hoppers for primary crushing.\r\n\r\n<strong>Wagon Tipplers</strong>\r\n\r\nIn Coal Handling Plants which are distant from Mines the ROM Coal is brought by rail and unloaded into Hoppers by Wagon Tipplers.\r\n\r\n<strong>Paddle Feeders</strong>\r\n\r\nThese are used for continuous reclaiming of coal from long length coal hoppers on to conveyors for further processing.\r\n\r\n<strong>Bucket Wheel Stacker cum Reclaimers</strong>\r\n\r\nThese are used in Coal/ Lignite Handling Plants to create large ground stockpiles of coal/ lignite and also to reclaim from the stockpile.', 'COAL & LIGNITE', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '607-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-06-22 06:31:19', '2015-06-22 06:31:19', '', 607, 'http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/607-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
