(1510, 2, '2015-06-22 08:11:10', '2015-06-22 08:11:10', '<strong>Aggregate Production is consisting of following activities-</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Extraction</strong>\r\n<p style="padding-left: 30px;">Stripping</p>\r\n<p style="padding-left: 30px;">Drilling &amp; Blasting</p>\r\n<p style="padding-left: 30px;">Shot Rock or Gravel Bank creation</p>\r\n<strong>Crushing</strong>\r\n<p style="padding-left: 30px;">Scalping</p>\r\n<p style="padding-left: 30px;">Primary Crushing</p>\r\n<p style="padding-left: 30px;">Secondary &amp; tertiary crushing</p>\r\n<p style="padding-left: 30px;">Impact Crushing</p>\r\n<strong>Screening</strong>\r\n\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;">Sizing &amp; Grading.</span>\r\n\r\n<strong>Sand Production</strong>\r\n\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;">Crushed sand of size 0-2.36 and 0-4.75 mm</span>\r\n\r\n<strong> Segregation</strong>\r\n\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;"> Its screening process depends on products size</span>\r\n\r\n<strong> Stockpiling &amp; Handling</strong>\r\n\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;"> Finished product stock of various size</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;"> Stocking bins of various size</span>\r\n\r\n<strong> Retrieval</strong>\r\n\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;"> Final products of Aggregates of various sizes</span>\r\n\r\nFollowing MSEL equipment cater to above processes in <span style="text-decoration: underline;"><em><strong>Aggregate Production-</strong></em></span>\r\n\r\n<a title="Apron Feeder" href="http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Apron-Feeder.pdf" target="_blank"><strong>Apron Feeders</strong></a>\r\n\r\nThese are extensively used to reclaim ROM/ Large Size rocks from Dump Hoppers for primary crushing at quarry end Stone Handling.\r\n\r\n<a title="Jaw Crusher" href="http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Jaw-Crusher.pdf" target="_blank"><strong>Jaw Crushers</strong></a>\r\n\r\nThese are used as primary crushers in aggregate production. Either Single Toggle or Double Toggle Jaw Crushers are selected based on hardness and mineralogy of stones.\r\n\r\n<a title="Double Roll Crusher" href="http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Double-Roll-Crusher.pdf" target="_blank"><strong>Roll Crushers</strong></a>\r\n\r\nToothed Double roll crusher are used as secondary crushers in aggregate plants to crush (-) 25 mm size and smooth double roll crushers can be used for producing (-) 5 mm size of soft and medium soft rock.\r\n\r\n<strong>Cone Crushers &amp; VSI</strong>\r\n\r\nMSEL has agency agreements with reputed manufacturers to sell these equipment, which are required in secondary crushing to produce aggregate of size 0 – 40 mm and 0 - 63 mm (GSB) &amp; tertiary crushing (-30/ 10 mm) of stones for subsequent reduction to even smaller sizes.\r\n\r\n<strong>Bucket Elevators</strong>\r\n\r\nThese are used for vertical transport of powdery, small grained bulk materials e.g. raw meal, cement, sand, grits, Salt etc.\r\n\r\n<strong> Conveying system &amp; Conveyor Components</strong>\r\n\r\nMSEL product range includes all types of drive and non-drive pulleys, and idlers. Conveying systems are designed based on capacity, type of material &amp; stocking criteria\r\n\r\n<strong>Reciprocating Feeders</strong>\r\n\r\nThese are built for high capacity reclamation from surge bins, bunker and hoppers. A wide range of sizes is available in MSEL offerings. Heavy Duty versions with larger drives and heavier pans can be selected for coarse Stones and normal versions for fine Stones.\r\n\r\n<strong> Rotary Disc Feeders</strong>\r\n\r\nThese are continuous volumetric device reclaiming dry small lumps, coarse, fine grained and powdery material e.g. river bed gravel, sand, alumina etc. from surge bins and hoppers to feed subsequent equipment.\r\n\r\n<strong>Grizzly Screens/ Feeders</strong>\r\n\r\nThese are used in primary crusher operation in Quarry Mining as scalping screen downstream of the Primary Crusher to separate undersized and oversized Stone. This also separate fines/dust from the feed before crushing &amp; avoid contamination. Typical separation is at 80 mm. These are also used as Feeders to reclaim Stone from Hoppers/Bins.\r\n\r\n<a title="Circular Motion" href="http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Circular-Motion.pdf" target="_blank"><strong>Circular Motion Screens</strong></a>\r\n\r\nAlso known as CM Screens, these are used to segregate various size fractions in Stone streams. Sometimes used to reduce load on crushers by removing fraction which is already smaller than required size and at other times these are used to recirculate oversize fractions from crushed product stream back to the crusher. These Screens are available in 1, 2 and 3 decks to get 2, 3 and 4 size fractions respectively. Each size fraction may be requiring different post processing.\r\n\r\n<a title="Linear Motion Screen" href="http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Linear-Motion-Screen1.pdf" target="_blank"><strong> Linear Motion Screens</strong></a>\r\n\r\n<a title="Linear Motion Screen" href="http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Linear-Motion-Screen1.pdf" target="_blank"> Linear Motion Screens</a> are used for similar applications but in more demanding situations, e.g.-\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Where the height is limited by surrounding facilities,</li>\r\n	<li>For the screening of small and short fractions</li>\r\n	<li>Where required throughput is high.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<a title="High Particle Acceleration HPA Screen" href="http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/High-Particle-Acceleration-HPA-Screen.pdf" target="_blank"><strong>High Particle Acceleration Screens</strong></a>\r\n\r\nThese are ideally suited for heavy and very heavy screening applications for fine grain size materials (3 mm to 10 mm) with screening capacities up to 250 metric TPH. The Inner frame is agitated by means of eccentric shaft drive. The vibration is passed on to the Outer frame via flexible thrust plates.\r\nScreening mats between the inner and outer frame are clamped and flexed by the two vibrating frames. The relative movement of both screening frames creates a “trampoline effect” in the screen mats to create-\r\n<ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>High acceleration up to 50g in screen mats.</li>\r\n	<li>Loosening-up and de-agglomeration of the product.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Banana Screens</strong>\r\n\r\nThese are multi-slope vibrating screens, come in single/ two deck configurations and are used in place of Circular Motion Screens when higher capacities (above 400 tph) are to be processed. The angle of deck decreases from feed end to discharge end.\r\n\r\n<a title="Mobile Crushing Screening Plant" href="http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Mobile-Crushing-Screening-Plant.pdf" target="_blank"><strong> Mobile &amp; Semi-mobile Crushing &amp; Screening Plants</strong></a>\r\n\r\nMSEL has a large range of <a title="Skid Mounted Crushing Plant" href="http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Skid-Mounted-Crushing-Plant1.pdf" target="_blank">skid mounted</a> and <a title="Skid Mounted Crushing Plant" href="http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Skid-Mounted-Crushing-Plant1.pdf" target="_blank">wheel mounted Crushing &amp; Screening plants</a> in various configurations to suit multiplicity of sized products in various capacities catering to production of coarse, medium and fine aggregates and road stratum material.\r\n\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Sand Plants</strong></span>\r\n\r\nMSEL Roll Crushers are suitable for making crushed sand. Roll crushers are suitable in secondary &amp; tertiary stage.\r\n\r\nFor <strong><em><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Infrastructure sector</span></em></strong> MSEL offers following equipment\r\n\r\n<a title="FB Series Dry Motar" href="http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/FB-Series-Dry-Motar1.pdf" target="_blank"> <strong>Dry Mortar Mixing Plants</strong></a>\r\n\r\nMSEL-NFLG <a title="FB Series Dry Motar" href="http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/FB-Series-Dry-Motar1.pdf" target="_blank">Dry Mortar Mixing</a> Plants are environment friendly and characterised by High Efficiency, Low Energy Consumption. The range Tower, Ladder and Station configurations covering a production range of 5 t/h to 80 t/h.\r\n\r\nFrom these plants basic grade and technical grade mortars are produced which are used as:\r\n\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;">Basic Grade</span> – Masonry mortar, wall render, base plaster, floor screed\r\n\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;">Technical grade</span> – Decorative plaster, tile adhesive, tile grout, water proofing, self levelling and thermal insulation\r\n\r\n<a title="Concrete Batching Plant" href="http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Concrete-Batching-Plant1.pdf" target="_blank"><strong>Concrete Batching Plants</strong></a>\r\n\r\nMSEL-NFLG <a title="Mobile Concrete Mixing Plant" href="http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Mobile-Crushing-Screening-Plant.pdf" target="_blank">Concrete Batching</a> Plants are available in Station and Tower configurations covering production capacity range of 60 m3/h to 270 m3/h\r\n\r\n<a title="Asphalt Mixing Plant" href="http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Asphalt-Mixing-Plant.pdf" target="_blank"><strong>Asphalt Batching Plants</strong></a>\r\n\r\nOur offerings in this sector cover mobile plants of 90 to 120 t/h and stationery plants of 80 to 400 t/h production capacities. Asphalt recycling plants have capacities of 60-160 t/h.\r\n\r\n<a title="Mobile Concrete Mixing Plant" href="http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Mobile-Concrete-Mixing-Plant.pdf" target="_blank"><strong>Mobile Concrete Batching Plants</strong></a>\r\n\r\nMSEL-NFLG mobile concrete mixing plants are available in 50, 75 and 100 m3/h capacities.\r\n\r\n<strong>Sand Washing Plant:</strong>\r\n\r\nWe can offer the sand washing plant with the water recovery equipment for the best quality of sand production with conservation of environment. We can offer the customised solution for any size/ capacity as most of the equipment used in this plant ie Thickener, Slurry pump and Filtration System are our regular product.\r\n\r\n<strong>Stone Cutting and Polishing Plant</strong>\r\n\r\nWe can give total solution for the slurry handling and ETP of the stone industry. We have the slurry pumps for the Grit recirculation, vertical slurry pumps for the water collection/ pumping, settlers, Flocculent dosing system and filter press under one roof.', 'AGGREGATE & INFRASTRUCTURE', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '635-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-06-22 08:11:10', '2015-06-22 08:11:10', '', 635, 'http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/635-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1511, 2, '2015-06-22 08:17:47', '2015-06-22 08:17:47', 'In a Thermal Power Plant, <strong>MSEL</strong> can supply variety of equipment under <strong>Balance of Plant</strong> (BOP) package.\r\nMSEL’s manufacturing range for BOP equipment includes the following:\r\na.  Motorized Trippers\r\nThese devices are mounted on conveyor belts running on top of long bunkers with several compartments and are used to discharge the material from the conveyor equitably all along the length of the bunker.\r\n\r\nb.  <a href="http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Rotary-Braker.pdf" target="_blank"><strong>Rotary Breaker</strong></a>\r\n\r\nRotary Breaker is used to separate hard rocks from coal while crushing the ROM ( below 600 mm) to (150-200 mm) in situations where coal’s hardness is significantly lower to that of contaminating stones/rocks.\r\n\r\nc.  <strong><a href="http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Ring-Granulator.pdf" target="_blank">Ring Granulator</a></strong>\r\n\r\nThis is a special purpose crusher for producing (-) 25 mm granular coal from (-) 250 mm feed, and is commonly used in Coal Handling Plants of Thermal Power Stations in all types of Coal Combustion systems.\r\n\r\n<strong>d.  Screening Feeder</strong>\r\n\r\nThese are screens entrusted with two tasks; that of feeding to Crushers and of pre-screening or scalping the feed to crushers. These may be of <strong>Linear Motion Screen</strong> with Geared Exciters or of Twin Eccentric Shaft in Oil Bath type.\r\n\r\n<strong>e. </strong> <a href="http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Apron-Feeder.pdf" target="_blank"><strong>Apron Feeder</strong></a>\r\n\r\nThese are extensively used to reclaim ROM/ Large Size Coal from Dump Hoppers for primary crushing.\r\n\r\n<strong>f.  Wagon Tippler</strong>\r\n\r\nIn Coal Handling Plants which are distant from Mines the ROM Coal is brought by rail and unloaded into Hoppers by Wagon Tipplers.\r\n\r\n<strong>g.  Paddle Feeder</strong>\r\n\r\nThese are used for continuous reclaiming of coal from long length track hoppers on to conveyors for further processing.\r\n\r\n<strong>h.  Stacker cum Reclaimer</strong>\r\n\r\nThese are used in Coal/Lignite Handling Plants to create large ground stockpiles of coal/lignite and also to reclaim from the stockpile as and when required.\r\n\r\n<strong>i.  Pulleys &amp; Idlers</strong>\r\n\r\nMSEL has all types of belt conveyor Pulleys and Idlers in its product range.\r\n\r\n<strong>j. Job Shop Manufactured Items</strong>\r\n\r\nMSEL has a huge facility to manufacture any types of fabricated and machining job as per the drawings supplied by the client.\r\n\r\n<strong>ASH HANDLING</strong>\r\n\r\nMSEL can supply following equipment for this sector.\r\na.  Transporter Vessel -- An air lock device to transfer ash from hoppers at atmospheric pressure to the pressurised conveying line.\r\nb.  Rotary Drum Mixer-- Conditions ash with water to minimize dust nuisance during unloading, feeds ash to open trucks or rail cars.\r\nc.  Paddle Mixer - Conditions ash with water to minimize dust nuisance during unloading, feeds ash to open trucks or rail cars. Nuisance mitigation ability of fugitive dust is more compared to Rotary Drum Mixer.\r\nd.   Ash Intake Valve – Controls ash flow with a swing disc gate, receiving the ash through an adapter hopper. An outlet tee connects the hopper to the conveyor line.\r\ne.  Air Intake Valve—Permits conveying air to enter the conveyor line. It may be adjusted to compensate for the negative pressure in the precipitator bag house.\r\nf.  Cup Valve – Allows ash flow into the Transporter Vessel avoiding avalanche of large amount of ash from collection hoppers by an uniquely designed cone inside the Valve housing.\r\ng.  Dual Disc Valve – Used as a speciality valve in dry ash conveying lines. Uniquely designed for usage in dry ash lines and has high abrasion resistant abilities which normal valves available in the market can’t offer.\r\nh.  Clinker Grinder -- It breaks up clinkers before transfer to the sluice pump. It may have single eccentric cam structure or double rolls to crush large sized ash lumps coming from furnace ash collection hopper..\r\ni.  Bag Filter -- Separates fine ash, not removed by the cyclonic separating equipment, from conveying air, prevents damage to mechanical vacuum producers and satisfies emission requirements.\r\nj.  Cyclone Separator/ Continuous Operating Separator – Separates ash from conveying air and deposits the ash in the bin without interrupting the conveying from the fly ash intakes. Lower capacity systems can use gravity dump units that briefly interrupt the conveying sequence to deposit the ash in the bin.\r\nk.  Vent Filter – The conveying air is vented back to the dust collector inlet, ash gets arrested in the bags of the filter and clean air vented to the atmosphere.\r\nl.  Centrifugal Ash Slurry Pumps—a centrifugal pump with required flow and discharge head used for transportation of abrasive ash slurry to ash pond or any abandoned place.\r\nm.  Sump Pumps – A centrifugal slurry pump executed in vertical disposition to pump out contaminated drain water collected in the plant.\r\nn.  Drag Chain Conveyors – An en-masse conveyor to transport dry ash in high capacities and to a relatively longer distance than normal dry ash conveyors carry.\r\no.  Air Receiver – Used as air storage tank to augment immediate surge air requirement for actuation of various valves, conveying lines, bag filter purging etc.', 'POWER', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '629-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-06-22 08:17:47', '2015-06-22 08:17:47', '', 629, 'http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/629-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1512, 2, '2015-06-22 08:28:10', '2015-06-22 08:28:10', 'Mineral Beneficiation is defined as the process of separating valuable minerals from waste gangue material in the mined ores. MSEL serves mineral beneficiation sectors of mining and minerals industry by supplying various equipment needed in beneficiation circuit as listed below.\r\nCircular Motion Screens\r\nThese Screens are used to segregate various size fractions in various mineral streams. Sometimes these are used to reduce load on crushers by removing fraction which is already smaller than required size and sometimes these are used to recirculate oversize fractions from crushed product stream back to crushers. Possible application is in Mines before despatch to power plants. These Screens are available in 1, 2 and 3 decks to get 2, 3 and 4 size fractions respectively. Each size fraction may be requiring different post processing.\r\nLinear Motion Screens\r\nLinear Motion Screens are used for similar applications but in more demanding situations, e.g.-\r\nWhere the height is limited by surrounding facilities,\r\nFor the screening of small and short fractions\r\nWhere required throughput is high.\r\n\r\nRoller Screens\r\nAs opposed to above two types which are based on bed stratification principle, Roller Screens are based on free fall principle. These are used in screening Run of Mine ore when feed stream consists of sticky, clayey, moist materials and would choke or blind the screen apertures of normal screening machines. It is also good for handling feed material containing larger boulders with smaller particles.\r\nGrizzly Feeders/Vibrating Feeders\r\nThese Feeders are used to reclaim feed stream from storage bins/ hoppers or as a feeding equipment to crusher &amp; screens where the materials are not easy to handle (wet, clayey or lot of ash content), having size fractions ranging from big lumps to significantly high percentage of wet/moist fines and where scalping is also needed.\r\nMotorised Trippers\r\nThese devices are mounted on conveyor belts running on top of long bunkers with several compartments and are used to discharge the material from the conveyor equitably all along the length of the bunker.\r\nRoll Crushers\r\nIn Ore Preparation Plants the feed is to be further crushed to (-) 25 mm size after primary crushing by using corrugated Double Roll Crushers. Smooth Double Roll Crushers can be used normally for crushing up to (-) 5mm.\r\nCone Crushers\r\nMSEL has agency agreements with reputed manufacturers to sell this equipment, which are required in secondary or tertiary crushing of various ores for subsequent grinding to even smaller sizes.\r\n\r\nImpactors (Heavy Duty Impactor)\r\nFor higher capacities and higher reduction of size, impactors/hammer mills are used.\r\nReciprocating Feeders\r\nThese are used to reclaim ore from surge bins/ bunkers to feed crushers or conveyors up to any desired capacity.\r\nRotary Disc Feeders\r\nThese are continuous volumetric device reclaiming dry small lumps, coarse, fine grained and powdery material from surge bins and hoppers to feed subsequent equipment. These can be used in chemical conditioning slurry tanks for dosing reagents.\r\nSlurry Pumps\r\nIn mines and ore handling plants these are used for dewatering the sump pits. In beneficiation plants these are used in conveying ore slurries from and to various units of beneficiation circuit.\r\nThickeners\r\nThese are used in Beneficiation Circuits to dewater/ thicken coal/reject slurries for further processing use.\r\nColumn Flotation Cells\r\nThese are used in beneficiation of Ore fines (&lt; 100 microns) where gravity and conventional flotation are not effective.\r\nU - Flotation Cells\r\nThese are used to concentrate and separate valuable minerals from gangue minerals or from other valuable minerals in beneficiation circuits.\r\nApron Feeders\r\nThese are extensively used to reclaim ROM/ Large Size feed lump from Dump Hoppers for primary crushing.\r\nConveyor Components\r\nMSEL product range includes all types of drive and non-drive pulleys, and idlers.\r\nDrum Scrubbers (Rotary Scrubber)\r\nThese are used to clean clayey/siliceous coatings from iron ore lumps as the first stage of Iron Ore Beneficiation.\r\n\r\nHigh Particle Acceleration Screens\r\nThese are ideally suited for screening applications for for higher level of moisture and fine grain size materials (1 mm to 10 mm) with screening capacities up to 250 metric TPH. The base frame is agitated by means of eccentric shaft drive. The vibration is passed on to the dynamic frame via thrust rubbers.\r\nScreening mats between the inner and outer frame are clamped and flexed by the two vibrating frames. The relative movement of both screening frames creates a “trampoline effect” in the screen mats to create-\r\nHigh acceleration up to 50g in screen mats.\r\nLoosening-up and de-agglomeration of the product.\r\nRoller Screens\r\nAs opposed to above three types of screens which are based on bed stratification principle, Roller Screens are based on free fall principle. These are used in Iron Ore Pellet Plants when it is essential to prevent breakage and degradation of pellets and efficient separation of fines for recycling back to pelletisers. It is also good for handling feed material containing larger boulder mixed with smaller particles.\r\nGrizzly Screens\r\nThese are used in primary crusher operation in Iron Ore Mining as scalping screen downstream of the Primary Ore Crusher to separate undersized and oversized ore. Typical separation is at 80 mm. These are also used as Feeders to reclaim ore from Hoppers/Bins.', 'MINERAL BENEFICIATION', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '625-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-06-22 08:28:10', '2015-06-22 08:28:10', '', 625, 'http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/625-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1513, 2, '2015-06-23 06:34:39', '2015-06-23 06:34:39', '<strong>Mineral Beneficiation is defined as the process of separating valuable minerals from waste gangue material in the mined ores. MSEL serves mineral beneficiation sectors of mining and minerals industry by supplying various equipment needed in beneficiation circuit as listed below.</strong>\n\n<a title="Circular Motion" href="http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Circular-Motion.pdf" target="_blank"><strong>Circular Motion Screens</strong></a>\n\nThese Screens are used to segregate various size fractions in various mineral streams. Sometimes these are used to reduce load on crushers by removing fraction which is already smaller than required size and sometimes these are used to recirculate oversize fractions from crushed product stream back to crushers. Possible application is in Mines before despatch to power plants. These Screens are available in 1, 2 and 3 decks to get 2, 3 and 4 size fractions respectively. Each size fraction may be requiring different post processing.\n\n<a title="Linear Motion Screen" href="http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Linear-Motion-Screen1.pdf" target="_blank"><strong>Linear Motion Screens</strong></a>\n\n<a title="Linear Motion Screen" href="http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Linear-Motion-Screen1.pdf" target="_blank">Linear Motion Screens</a> are used for similar applications but in more demanding situations, e.g.-\nWhere the height is limited by surrounding facilities,\nFor the screening of small and short fractions\nWhere required throughput is high.\n\n<a href="http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Roller-Screen.pdf" target="_blank"><strong>Roller Screens</strong></a>\n\nAs opposed to above two types which are based on bed stratification principle, <a title="Roller Screen" href="http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Roller-Screen.pdf" target="_blank">Roller Screens</a> are based on free fall principle. These are used in screening Run of Mine ore when feed stream consists of sticky, clayey, moist materials and would choke or blind the screen apertures of normal screening machines. It is also good for handling feed material containing larger boulders with smaller particles.\n\n<strong>Grizzly Feeders/Vibrating Feeders</strong>\n\nThese Feeders are used to reclaim feed stream from storage bins/ hoppers or as a feeding equipment to crusher &amp; screens where the materials are not easy to handle (wet, clayey or lot of ash content), having size fractions ranging from big lumps to significantly high percentage of wet/moist fines and where scalping is also needed.\n\n<strong>Motorised Trippers</strong>\n\nThese devices are mounted on conveyor belts running on top of long bunkers with several compartments and are used to discharge the material from the conveyor equitably all along the length of the bunker.\n\n<strong><a href="http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Single-Roll-Crusher.pdf" target="_blank">Roll Crushers</a></strong>\n\nIn Ore Preparation Plants the feed is to be further crushed to (-) 25 mm size after primary crushing by using corrugated<a href="http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Double-Roll-Crusher.pdf" target="_blank"> Double Roll Crushers</a>. <a href="http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Smooth-Roll-Crusher.pdf" target="_blank">Smooth Double Roll</a> Crushers can be used <strong>normally</strong> for crushing up to (-) 5mm.\n\n<strong>Cone Crushers</strong>\n\nMSEL has agency agreements with reputed manufacturers to sell this equipment, which are required in secondary or tertiary crushing of various ores for subsequent grinding to even smaller sizes.\n\n<strong><a href="http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Heavy-Duty-Impactor.pdf" target="_blank">Impactors</a> (Heavy Duty Impactor)</strong>\n\nFor higher capacities and higher reduction of size, impactors/hammer mills are used.\n\n<strong>Reciprocating Feeders</strong>\n\nThese are used to reclaim ore from surge bins/ bunkers to feed crushers or conveyors up to any desired capacity.\n\n<strong>Rotary Disc Feeders</strong>\n\nThese are continuous volumetric device reclaiming dry small lumps, coarse, fine grained and powdery material from surge bins and hoppers to feed subsequent equipment. These can be used in chemical conditioning slurry tanks for dosing reagents.\n\n<strong><a href="http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Slurry-Pumps.pdf" target="_blank">Slurry Pumps</a></strong>\n\nIn mines and ore handling plants these are used for dewatering the sump pits. In beneficiation plants these are used in conveying ore slurries from and to various units of beneficiation circuit.\n\n<strong><a href="http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Thickener.pdf" target="_blank">Thickeners</a></strong>\n\nThese are used in Beneficiation Circuits to dewater/ thicken coal/reject slurries for further processing use.\n\n<strong><a href="http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Column-Flotation-Cell.pdf" target="_blank">Column Flotation Cells</a></strong>\n\nThese are used in beneficiation of Ore fines (&lt; 100 microns) where gravity and conventional flotation are not effective.\n\nU -<strong><a href="http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Flotation-CELL.pdf" target="_blank"> Flotation Cells</a></strong>\n\nThese are used to concentrate and separate valuable minerals from gangue minerals or from other valuable minerals in beneficiation circuits.\n\n<a href="http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Apron-Feeder.pdf"><strong>Apron Feeders</strong></a>\n\nThese are extensively used to reclaim ROM/ Large Size feed lump from Dump Hoppers for primary crushing.\n\n<strong>Conveyor Components</strong>\n\nMSEL product range includes all types of drive and non-drive pulleys, and idlers.\n\n<strong><a title="Rotary Scrubber" href="http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Rotary-Scrubber.pdf" target="_blank">Drum Scrubbers</a> (Rotary Scrubber)</strong>\n\nThese are used to clean clayey/siliceous coatings from iron ore lumps as the first stage of Iron Ore Beneficiation.\n\n<strong><a href="http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/High-Particle-Acceleration-HPA-Screen.pdf">High Particle Acceleration Screens</a></strong>\n\nThese are ideally suited for screening applications for <strong>higher level of moisture and</strong> fine grain size materials (1 mm to 10 mm) with screening capacities up to 250 metric TPH. The base frame is agitated by means of eccentric shaft drive. The vibration is passed on to the dynamic frame via thrust rubbers.\nScreening mats between the inner and outer frame are clamped and flexed by the two vibrating frames. The relative movement of both screening frames creates a “trampoline effect” in the screen mats to create-\n<ul>\n	<li>High acceleration up to 50g in screen mats.</li>\n	<li>Loosening-up and de-agglomeration of the product.</li>\n</ul>\n<strong><a href="http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Roller-Screen.pdf">Roller Screens</a></strong>\n\nAs opposed to above three types of screens which are based on bed stratification principle, Roller Screens are based on free fall principle. These are used in Iron Ore Pellet Plants when it is essential to prevent breakage and degradation of pellets and efficient separation of fines for recycling back to pelletisers. <strong><em>It is also good for handling feed material containing larger boulder mixed with smaller particles.</em></strong>\n\n<strong>Grizzly Screens</strong>\n\nThese are used in primary crusher operation in Iron Ore Mining as scalping screen downstream of the Primary Ore Crusher to separate undersized and oversized ore. Typical separation is at 80 mm. These are also used as Feeders to reclaim ore from Hoppers/Bins.', 'MINERAL BENEFICIATION', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '625-autosave-v1', '', '', '2015-06-23 06:34:39', '2015-06-23 06:34:39', '', 625, 'http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/625-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1514, 2, '2015-06-22 08:54:50', '2015-06-22 08:54:50', '<strong>Mineral Beneficiation is defined as the process of separating valuable minerals from waste gangue material in the mined ores. MSEL serves mineral beneficiation sectors of mining and minerals industry by supplying various equipment needed in beneficiation circuit as listed below.</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Circular Motion Screens</strong>\r\n\r\nThese Screens are used to segregate various size fractions in various mineral streams. Sometimes these are used to reduce load on crushers by removing fraction which is already smaller than required size and sometimes these are used to recirculate oversize fractions from crushed product stream back to crushers. Possible application is in Mines before despatch to power plants. These Screens are available in 1, 2 and 3 decks to get 2, 3 and 4 size fractions respectively. Each size fraction may be requiring different post processing.\r\n\r\n<strong>Linear Motion Screens</strong>\r\n\r\nLinear Motion Screens are used for similar applications but in more demanding situations, e.g.-\r\nWhere the height is limited by surrounding facilities,\r\nFor the screening of small and short fractions\r\nWhere required throughput is high.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Roller-Screen.pdf" target="_blank"><strong>Roller Screens</strong></a>\r\n\r\nAs opposed to above two types which are based on bed stratification principle, Roller Screens are based on free fall principle. These are used in screening Run of Mine ore when feed stream consists of sticky, clayey, moist materials and would choke or blind the screen apertures of normal screening machines. It is also good for handling feed material containing larger boulders with smaller particles.\r\n\r\n<strong>Grizzly Feeders/Vibrating Feeders</strong>\r\n\r\nThese Feeders are used to reclaim feed stream from storage bins/ hoppers or as a feeding equipment to crusher &amp; screens where the materials are not easy to handle (wet, clayey or lot of ash content), having size fractions ranging from big lumps to significantly high percentage of wet/moist fines and where scalping is also needed.\r\n\r\n<strong>Motorised Trippers</strong>\r\n\r\nThese devices are mounted on conveyor belts running on top of long bunkers with several compartments and are used to discharge the material from the conveyor equitably all along the length of the bunker.\r\n\r\n<strong><a href="http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Single-Roll-Crusher.pdf" target="_blank">Roll Crushers</a></strong>\r\n\r\nIn Ore Preparation Plants the feed is to be further crushed to (-) 25 mm size after primary crushing by using corrugated<a href="http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Double-Roll-Crusher.pdf" target="_blank"> Double Roll Crushers</a>. <a href="http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Smooth-Roll-Crusher.pdf" target="_blank">Smooth Double Roll</a> Crushers can be used normally for crushing up to (-) 5mm.\r\n\r\n<strong>Cone Crushers</strong>\r\n\r\nMSEL has agency agreements with reputed manufacturers to sell this equipment, which are required in secondary or tertiary crushing of various ores for subsequent grinding to even smaller sizes.\r\n\r\nImpactors (Heavy Duty Impactor)\r\nFor higher capacities and higher reduction of size, impactors/hammer mills are used.\r\nReciprocating Feeders\r\nThese are used to reclaim ore from surge bins/ bunkers to feed crushers or conveyors up to any desired capacity.\r\nRotary Disc Feeders\r\nThese are continuous volumetric device reclaiming dry small lumps, coarse, fine grained and powdery material from surge bins and hoppers to feed subsequent equipment. These can be used in chemical conditioning slurry tanks for dosing reagents.\r\nSlurry Pumps\r\nIn mines and ore handling plants these are used for dewatering the sump pits. In beneficiation plants these are used in conveying ore slurries from and to various units of beneficiation circuit.\r\nThickeners\r\nThese are used in Beneficiation Circuits to dewater/ thicken coal/reject slurries for further processing use.\r\nColumn Flotation Cells\r\nThese are used in beneficiation of Ore fines (&lt; 100 microns) where gravity and conventional flotation are not effective.\r\nU - Flotation Cells\r\nThese are used to concentrate and separate valuable minerals from gangue minerals or from other valuable minerals in beneficiation circuits.\r\nApron Feeders\r\nThese are extensively used to reclaim ROM/ Large Size feed lump from Dump Hoppers for primary crushing.\r\nConveyor Components\r\nMSEL product range includes all types of drive and non-drive pulleys, and idlers.\r\nDrum Scrubbers (Rotary Scrubber)\r\nThese are used to clean clayey/siliceous coatings from iron ore lumps as the first stage of Iron Ore Beneficiation.\r\n\r\nHigh Particle Acceleration Screens\r\nThese are ideally suited for screening applications for for higher level of moisture and fine grain size materials (1 mm to 10 mm) with screening capacities up to 250 metric TPH. The base frame is agitated by means of eccentric shaft drive. The vibration is passed on to the dynamic frame via thrust rubbers.\r\nScreening mats between the inner and outer frame are clamped and flexed by the two vibrating frames. The relative movement of both screening frames creates a “trampoline effect” in the screen mats to create-\r\nHigh acceleration up to 50g in screen mats.\r\nLoosening-up and de-agglomeration of the product.\r\nRoller Screens\r\nAs opposed to above three types of screens which are based on bed stratification principle, Roller Screens are based on free fall principle. These are used in Iron Ore Pellet Plants when it is essential to prevent breakage and degradation of pellets and efficient separation of fines for recycling back to pelletisers. It is also good for handling feed material containing larger boulder mixed with smaller particles.\r\nGrizzly Screens\r\nThese are used in primary crusher operation in Iron Ore Mining as scalping screen downstream of the Primary Ore Crusher to separate undersized and oversized ore. Typical separation is at 80 mm. These are also used as Feeders to reclaim ore from Hoppers/Bins.', 'MINERAL BENEFICIATION', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '625-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-06-22 08:54:50', '2015-06-22 08:54:50', '', 625, 'http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/625-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
