me is agitated by means of eccentric shaft drive. The vibration is passed on to the inner frame via flexible thrust plates.\r\n\r\nScreening mats between the inner and outer frame are clamped and flexed by the two vibrating frames. The relative movement of both screening frames creates a “trampoline effect” in the screen mats to create-\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>High acceleration up to 50g in screen mats.</li>\r\n	<li>Loosening-up and de-agglomeration of the product.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Banana Screens</strong>\r\n\r\nThese are multi-slope vibrating screens, come in single/ two/ three deck configurations and are used in place of Circular Motion Screens when higher capacities (above 400 tph) are to be processed. The angle of deck decreases from feed end to discharge end.\r\n\r\n<strong>Cone Crushers</strong>\r\n\r\nMSEL has agency agreements with reputed manufacturers to sell these equipment, which are required as Secondary (-150/ 75 mm) and Tertiary Crushers (-30/ 10 mm) in Bauxite Crushing for Alumina production.\r\n\r\n<strong>Reciprocating Feeders</strong>\r\n\r\nThese are built for high capacity reclamation from surge bins, bunker and hoppers and also as feeding equipment. A wide range of sizes is available in MSEL offerings. Heavy Duty versions with larger drives and heavier pans can be selected for coarse ores and normal versions for fine ores\r\n\r\n<strong>Bucket Elevators</strong>\r\n\r\nThese are used for vertical transport of powdery, small grained bulk materials e.g. raw meal, cement, sand, grits etc. They are used in filling tall bauxite and alumina silos.\r\n\r\n<a title="Slurry Pumps" href="http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Slurry-Pumps.pdf" target="_blank"><strong>Slurry Pumps</strong></a>\r\n\r\nIn Beneficiation plants usually the process involves transporting of Ore Slurry (suspension of Crushed/ Ground Ore in Water) between various stages. This is done by use of Slurry Pumps. MSEL has a vast range of Horizontal and Vertical Centrifugal Pumps catering to these requirements.\r\n\r\n<a title="Grinding Mill" href="http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Grinding-Mill.pdf" target="_blank"><strong>Rod Mills (Grinding Mill)</strong></a>\r\n\r\nFinal crushed ore from tertiary crushers is ground to (-) 1 mm by rod mills. MSEL has a large range of rod mills to suit most ore characteristics and product requirements.\r\n\r\n<a title="Grinding Mill" href="http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Grinding-Mill.pdf" target="_blank"><strong>Ball Mills (Grinding Mill)</strong></a>\r\n\r\nThese are used for size reduction to microns and form part of grinding circuit to get the final product for calcining or Alumina refining Process. These are also used in Coke Grinding for Carbon Paste preparation in Aluminium Smelters.\r\n\r\n<a title="Thickener" href="http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Thickener.pdf" target="_blank"><strong>Thickeners</strong></a>\r\n\r\nThese are used to concentrate alumina Slurry (30-35% Solids) from refinery to about 60- 70 % Solids. Overflow product is mostly water and is recycled into circuit whereas the underflow is taken for evaporation circuit or to tailings as reject disposal.\r\n\r\n<strong>Flotation</strong>\r\n\r\nWe can offer the Beneficiation/Up gradation solution for the Bauxite ore through flotation as part of total solution for this plant which will include Crushing, Grinding, Flotation, thickening, dewatering (Filtration), slurry pumping and system integration and plant design.', 'ALUMINIUM & BAUXITE', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '615-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-06-23 00:09:42', '2015-06-23 00:09:42', '', 615, 'http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/615-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1521, 2, '2015-06-23 00:12:17', '2015-06-23 00:12:17', '<strong><a href="http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Jaw-Crusher.pdf">Jaw Crushers</a></strong>\r\n\r\nThese are used as alternatives to Gyratory Crushers as primary crushers in Zinc, Lead, Copper and Gold Mining when the throughput needed is less than 500 - 600 metric TPH. For hard ores Double Toggle Jaw Crushers and for softer ores Single Toggle Jaw Crushers are customary.\r\n\r\n<strong><a href="http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Apron-Feeder.pdf">Apron Feeders</a></strong>\r\n\r\nThese are extensively used to reclaim ROM/ Large Size ores from Dump Hoppers for primary crushing at mine end Ore Handling.\r\n\r\n<strong>Motorised Trippers</strong>\r\n\r\nBasically these are rail mounted conveyor discharging equipment to uniformly distribute the conveyed Ore over a large Bin or Ground Storage stockpile.\r\n\r\n<strong>Cone Crushers</strong>\r\n\r\nMSEL has agency agreements with reputed manufacturers to sell this equipment, which are required as Secondary (150/ 75 mm) and Tertiary Crushers (30/10 mm) in Beneficiation circuits.\r\n\r\n<strong>Conveyor Components</strong>\r\n\r\nMSEL product range includes all types of drive and non-drive pulleys, and idlers.\r\n\r\n<strong><a href="http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Linear-Motion-Screen.pdf">Rod Mills </a>(Grinding Mill)</strong>\r\n\r\nIn most of Zn-Pb-Cu-Au mining circuits, final crushed ore from tertiary crushers is ground to (-) 1mm by rod mills. Where High Pressure Grinding Rolls are used secondary and tertiary crushing as well as rod milling is dispensed with. MSEL has a large range of rod mills to suit most ore characteristics and product requirements.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Grinding-Mill.pdf"><strong>Ball Mills</strong></a> (Grinding Mill)\r\n\r\nThese are used for size reduction to microns and form part of a grinding circuit in Ore Beneficiation Plant. In Zn-Pb-Cu-Au mining circuits ball mills grind rod mill products or products from High Pressure Grinding Rolls to (-) 75/40 microns and create slurry of 30-35 % solids concentration.\r\nThese are also used as regrind mills in Flotation Circuits.\r\n\r\n<strong>Circular Motion Screens</strong>\r\n\r\nCircular Motion Screens are used to segregate various size fractions in ore streams. Sometimes used to reduce load on crushers by removing fraction which is already smaller than required size and at other times these are used to recirculate oversize fractions from crushed product stream back to crushers. Possible application is in Mines before despatch to beneficiation plants and also in beneficiation plants. These Screens are available in 1, 2 and 3 decks to get 2, 3 and 4 size fractions respectively. Each size fraction may be requiring different post processing.\r\n\r\n<strong>Rotary Disc Feeders</strong>\r\n\r\nThese are continuous volumetric device reclaiming dry small lumps, coarse, fine grained and powdery material from surge bins and hoppers to feed subsequent equipment. These can be used in chemical conditioning slurry tanks for dosing reagents.\r\n\r\n<strong>Linear Motion Screens</strong>\r\n\r\nLinear Motion Screens are used for similar applications but in more demanding situations, e.g.-\r\nWhere the height is limited by surrounding facilities,\r\nFor the screening of small and short fractions\r\nWhere required throughput is high.\r\n\r\n<strong><a href="http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/High-Particle-Acceleration-HPA-Screen.pdf" target="_blank">High Particle Acceleration Screens</a></strong>\r\n\r\nThese are ideally suited for screening applications for for higher level of moisture and fine grain size materials (1 mm to 10 mm) with screening capacities up to 250 metric TPH. The Inner frame is agitated by means of eccentric shaft drive. The vibration is passed on to the Outer frame via thrust rubbers.\r\nScreening mats between the inner and outer frame are clamped and flexed by the two vibrating frames. The relative movement of both screening frames creates a “trampoline effect” in the screen mats to create-\r\nHigh acceleration up to 50g in screen mats.\r\nLoosening-up and de-agglomeration of the product.\r\n\r\n<strong>Banana Screens</strong>\r\n\r\nThese are multi-slope vibrating screens, come in single/ two/ three deck configurations and are used in place of Circular Motion Screens when higher capacities (above 400 tph) are to be processed. The angle of deck decreases from feed end to discharge end.\r\n\r\n<strong>Grizzly Screens</strong>\r\n\r\nThese are used in primary crushing operation as scalping screen in downstream of the Primary Ore Crusher to separate undersized and oversized ore. Typical separation is at 80 mm. These are also used as Feeders to reclaim ore from Hoppers/Bins.\r\n\r\n<strong>Reciprocating Feeders</strong>\r\n\r\nThese are built for high capacity reclamation from surge bins, bunker and hoppers and also as feeding equipment. A wide range of sizes is available in MSEL offerings. Heavy Duty versions with larger drives and heavier pans can be selected for coarse ores and normal versions for fine ores\r\n\r\n<strong><a href="http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Slurry-Pumps.pdf" target="_blank">Slurry Pumps</a></strong>\r\n\r\nIn Beneficiation plants usually the process involves transporting of Ore Slurry (suspension of Crushed/ Ground Ore in Water) between various stages. This is done by use of Slurry Pumps. MSEL has a vast range of Horizontal and Vertical Centrifugal Pumps catering to these requirements.\r\n\r\n<strong><a href="http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Thickener.pdf" target="_blank">Thickeners</a></strong>\r\n\r\nThese are used to concentrate Ore Slurry (30-35% Solids) from various stages of flotation to about 60- 70 % Solids. Overflow product is mostly water and is recycled into circuit whereas the underflow is taken for filtration (in case of Concentrate Thickeners) or to tailings as reject disposal.\r\n\r\n<strong><a href="http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Flotation-CELL.pdf" target="_blank">Flotation Cells</a></strong>\r\n\r\nThese are used for removal of specific impurities ore separation of different metallic particles from multi-metal ore slurries. Tests determine the size and configuration of the Flotation Cell Banks.\r\n\r\n<strong>Filter Press</strong>\r\n\r\nWe offer MSEL-Choquenet Filter Press for dewatering of concentrate or tailing in Beneficiation Circuits.', 'ZINC, LEAD, COPPER & GOLD', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '611-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-06-23 00:12:17', '2015-06-23 00:12:17', '', 611, 'http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/611-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
