xtensively used to reclaim ROM/ Large Size Limestone from Dump Hoppers for primary crushing.\r\n\r\n<strong>Conveyor Components</strong>\r\n\r\nMSEL product range includes all types of drive and non-drive pulleys, and idlers.\r\n\r\n<strong>Motorised Trippers</strong>\r\n\r\nBasically these are rail mounted conveyor discharging equipment to uniformly distribute the conveyed Ore over a large Bin or Ground Storage stockpile.\r\n\r\n<strong><a title="Rotary Scrubber" href="http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Rotary-Scrubber.pdf" target="_blank">Drum Scrubbers</a> (Rotary Scrubber)</strong>\r\n\r\nThese are used to clean clayey/siliceous coatings from ore lumps as the first stage of raw material preparation.\r\n\r\n<a title="Circular Motion" href="http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Circular-Motion.pdf" target="_blank"><strong>Circular Motion Screen</strong></a>\r\n\r\n<a title="Circular Motion" href="http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Circular-Motion.pdf" target="_blank">Circular Motion Screens</a> are used to segregate various size fractions in ore streams. Sometimes used to reduce load on crushers by removing fraction which is already smaller than required size at other times these are used to recirculate oversize fractions from crushed product stream back to crushers. Possible application is in Mines before despatch to beneficiation plants as also in beneficiation plants. These Screens are available in 1, 2 and 3 decks to get 2, 3 and 4 size fractions respectively. Each size fraction may be requiring different post processing.\r\n\r\n<a title="Linear Motion Screen" href="http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Linear-Motion-Screen1.pdf" target="_blank"><strong>Linear Motion Screens</strong></a>\r\n\r\nLinear Motion Screens are used for similar applications but in more demanding situations, e.g.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Where the height is limited by surrounding facilities,</li>\r\n	<li>For the screening of small and short fractions</li>\r\n	<li>Where required throughput is high.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<a title="High Particle Acceleration HPA Screen" href="http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/High-Particle-Acceleration-HPA-Screen.pdf" target="_blank"><strong>High Particle Acceleration Screens</strong></a>\r\n\r\nThese are ideally suited for screening applications for fine grain size materials (1 mm to 10 mm) with screening capacities up to 250 metric TPH. The base frame is agitated by means of eccentric shaft drive. The vibration is passed on to the dynamic frame via thrust rubbers.\r\nScreening mats between the inner and outer frame are clamped and flexed by the two vibrating frames. The relative movement of both screening frames creates a “trampoline effect” in the screen mats to create\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>High acceleration up to 50g in screen mats.</li>\r\n	<li>Loosening-up and de-agglomeration of the product.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Grizzly Screens</strong>\r\n\r\nThese are used in primary crushing circuit as scalping screen downstream of the Primary Ore Crusher to separate undersized and oversized ore. Typical separation is at 80 mm. These are also used as Feeders to reclaim ore from Hoppers/Bins.\r\n\r\n<strong>Flotation Cells</strong>\r\n\r\nWe can offer Flotation cells for the lime ore Beneficiation or silica removal.\r\n\r\nSlurry Pump\r\n\r\nSlurry Pump for capacity of 2500M3/Hr is available in our regular product range for use in Lime ore beneficiation and silica removal.\r\n\r\nThickener\r\n\r\nFor the thickening of the limestone slurry/ tailing etc. we can offer proven thickening solution customised for the process requirement.\r\n\r\nLime Stone Beneficiation Plant\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>We can offer the total limestone scrubbing plant with engineering for the small up gradation and removal of soil etc.</li>\r\n	<li>For the Low grade lime stone we can give the flotation Plant with all the equipment and engineering.</li>\r\n</ol>', 'CEMENT', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '633-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-06-23 00:41:18', '2015-06-23 00:41:18', '', 633, 'http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/633-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1529, 2, '2015-06-23 00:54:36', '2015-06-23 00:54:36', 'With production units at Kumardhubi (I and II), Asansol, Baroda and Bangalore, MSEL is well equipped to undertake job shop manufacturing of items, equipment and or machine components, vessels, heavy structural etc. to customer’s drawings and specifications. The overhead material handling capacity at our units range from 70 MT to 100 MT of EOT cranes and the roof has a hook height up to 13 meters. There is also adequate open yard space for open yard fabrication. The manufacturing facilities are well equipped to handle large jobs which require precision machining, welding and fabrication.\n\nAlmost all the major engineering houses of Europe have imposed trust on us. All the major steel manufacturers of the country are our customers. Our facilities are approved for IBR equipment and also approved by Nuclear Power Corporation and NTPC. Major third party inspection agencies like Lloyds, TPE, TUV etc. regularly visit us for inspection of on-going jobs.\n\n<strong>STEEL PLANT EQUIPMENT</strong>\n\nMSEL regularly manufactures to the design and drawings of companies like Siemens, Danieli, Danieli Corus, SMS Siemag, SMS Meer, Paul Wurth and others. Some of major items manufactured by us for Steel Plants are listed below\n<ul>\n	<li>EQUIPMENT FOR BILLET &amp; BLOOM CASTER\n<ul>\n	<li>ALL TYPES OF ROLLER TABLES</li>\n	<li>TAIL END PINCH ROLL</li>\n	<li>BILLET LIFTING DEVICE</li>\n	<li>TURN OVER COOLING BED</li>\n	<li>PUSHER ONTO ROLLER TABLE (MULTI STEP PUSHER)</li>\n	<li>DUMMY BAR STORAGE UNIT</li>\n	<li>CUTTING EQUIPMENT ( CROP DISCHARGE BUCKET, CROP COLLECTION ETC)</li>\n	<li>TUNDISH DESKULLING MACHINE, TUNDISH NOZZLE FIXING</li>\n	<li>TUNDIAH HANDLING TRAVERSE</li>\n	<li>MACHINE SUPPORT STRUCTURE</li>\n	<li>TUNDISH RELINING / COOLING STAND,TUNDISH TILTING DEVISE</li>\n	<li>STRAND GUIDE EQUIPMENT</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n	<li>EQUIPMENT FOR CONVERTER\n<ul>\n	<li>EMERGENCY LADLES, TEEMING LADLES</li>\n	<li>LADLE TRANSFER CAR, SCRAP BOX TRANSFER CARS</li>\n	<li>SCRUBBING TOWER COMPRISING OF SHELL AND INTERNAL CHANNELS, SEPARATOR, SEAL POTS, MANHOLES, QUENCHER VENTURI THROAT ETC. FOR WET GAS CLEANING OF BOF-GCP</li>\n	<li>HOOD TRAVERSE CARRIAGE</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n	<li>EQUIPMENT FOR BLAST FURNACE\n<ul>\n	<li>BLEEDER VALVE</li>\n	<li>DISTRIBUTION ROCKER</li>\n	<li>DISMANTLING DEVICE</li>\n	<li>DEWATERING DRUM AND SUPPORTING STRUCTURE</li>\n	<li>PROFILE METER</li>\n	<li>IN BURDEN PROBE</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<strong>STOCK YARD EQUIPMENT</strong>\n\nMSEL group company MBE has a technology collaboration agreement with FAMAK for wagon tippler, side arm charger to the latest specifications of RDSO, beside other equipment. Similarly, in association with Poltegor, MSEL through MBE, has manufactured several stacker cum reclaimers, including the largest in India for Adani Port (Mundra) of capacity 6000 x 2500 TPH with track gauge 10 meter and boom length of 41 meter.\n<ul>\n	<li>WAGON TIPPLER</li>\n	<li>SIDE ARM CHARGER</li>\n	<li>STACKER RECLAIMER</li>\n	<li>TRIPPER</li>\n	<li>BELT CONVEYORS AND COMPONENTS</li>\n	<li>GRAVITY ROLLER CONVEYOR</li>\n	<li>POWERED ROLLER CONVEYOR</li>\n	<li>EOT CRANES</li>\n	<li>PULLEYS AND IDLERS</li>\n</ul>\n<strong>PORT HANDLING EQUIPMENT</strong>\n\nMSEL has manufactured some of the largest Goliath cranes, including the one at Mazagon Dock, with a span of 138 meter, height of 65 meter and load carrying capacity of 300 MT, with technology from Kone through group company MBE. Similarly, ELL cranes of 45 MT capacity with a track gauge of 8 meters, radius 35 meters and maximum height of lift of 50 meters have been manufactured.\n<ul>\n	<li>BARGE UNLOADER</li>\n	<li>CONTAINER HANDLING CRANE</li>\n	<li>BULK HANDLING CRANE</li>\n	<li>SHIPYARD CRANE</li>\n	<li>ELL AND LLTT</li>\n	<li>GOLIATH CRANES</li>\n</ul>\n<strong>OPENCAST MINING EQUIPMENT</strong>\n\nMSEL group company MBE has technology collaboration with Poltegor for several mining equipment. Through that, MSEL has manufactured in its own manufacturing unit, the largest bucket wheel excavator of 700 liter capacity bucket wheel excavator of 1650 MT weight for Neyveli Lignite Corporation. Similarly, for the same customer, MSEL has manufactured crawler mounted spreader of 4420 cu meter/ hr of 950 MT weight and shiftable conveyor system of 20,000 TPH (highest in the country) with 2.4 meter wide conveyor belt (widest in the country).\n<ul>\n	<li>BUCKET WHEEL EXCAVATOR</li>\n	<li>CRAWLER MOUNTED SPREADER</li>\n	<li>SHIFTABLE CONVEYOR</li>\n</ul>\n<strong>ASH HANDLING EQUIPMENT</strong>\n\nWith technology from group companies MBE and EWB of Hungary, MSEL has manufactured several ash handling equipment including the following\n<ul>\n	<li>TRANSPORTER VESSEL</li>\n	<li>AIR RECEIVER</li>\n	<li>CLINKER CRUSHER</li>\n	<li>MIXER</li>\n	<li>SCRAPER CHAIN CONVEYOR</li>\n	<li>BAG FILTER</li>\n</ul>\nOTHER EQUIPMENT\n\nBeside the above, MSEL has manufactured at its manufacturing facility several other equipment for reputed customers like NTPC, METSO POWER, NPC, BHEL and others. The list of equipment includes\n\nPrimary Gas Cooler\nCoke Oven &amp; By Product Equipment\nElectrode Arms, Mast and lance for Lancing Furnace\nDucting and Gas Cooler Primary Scrubbers\nSlab Charging Buffer and Grate\nTube Heat Exchangers, Low Pressure and High Pressure Boilers\nSulphur Condensers and Process Gas Heater\nMachined and Tooth Cut Gears up to 8 M diameters\nReconditioning of HP/LP Feeder for Paper Industry.\nRotary Kiln components e.g. Shell, Slide Shoe, and Base Frame etc.\nPenstocks and Gates for Hydro-electric Plants.\nButt Extractors for Anode Plants.', 'JOBBING', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '637-autosave-v1', '', '', '2015-06-23 00:54:36', '2015-06-23 00:54:36', '', 637, 'http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/637-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
