(1639, 2, '2015-09-14 12:54:34', '2015-09-14 12:54:34', '<strong><a href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Jaw-Crusher.pdf">Jaw Crushers</a></strong>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Jaw-Crusher.pdf">Jaw Crushers</a> are used as alternatives to Gyratory Crushers as primary crushers in Zinc, Lead, Copper and Gold Mining when the throughput needed is less than 500 - 600 metric TPH. For hard ores Double Toggle Jaw Crushers and for softer ores Single Toggle Jaw Crushers are customary.\r\n\r\n<strong><a href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Apron-Feeder.pdf">Apron Feeders</a></strong>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Apron-Feeder.pdf">Apron Feeders</a> are extensively used to reclaim ROM/ Large Size ores from Dump Hoppers for primary crushing at mine end Ore Handling.\r\n\r\n<strong>Motorised Trippers</strong>\r\n\r\nBasically Motorised Trippers are rail mounted conveyor discharging equipment to uniformly distribute the conveyed Ore over a large Bin or Ground Storage stockpile.\r\n\r\n<strong>Cone Crushers</strong>\r\n\r\nMSEL has agency agreements with reputed manufacturers to sell this equipment, which are required as Secondary (150/ 75 mm) and Tertiary Crushers (30/10 mm) in Beneficiation circuits.\r\n\r\n<strong>Conveyor Components</strong>\r\n\r\nMSEL product range includes all types of drive and non-drive pulleys, and idlers.\r\n\r\n<strong><a title="Grinding Mill" href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Grinding-Mill.pdf" target="_blank">Rod Mills </a>(Grinding Mill)</strong>\r\n\r\nIn most of Zn-Pb-Cu-Au mining circuits, final crushed ore from tertiary crushers is ground to (-) 1mm by rod mills. Where High Pressure Grinding Rolls are used secondary and tertiary crushing as well as rod milling is dispensed with. MSEL has a large range of rod mills to suit most ore characteristics and product requirements.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Grinding-Mill.pdf"><strong>Ball Mills</strong></a> (Grinding Mill)\r\n\r\n<a href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Grinding-Mill.pdf">Ball Mills</a> (Grinding Mill) are used for size reduction to microns and form part of a grinding circuit in Ore Beneficiation Plant. In Zn-Pb-Cu-Au mining circuits ball mills grind rod mill products or products from High Pressure Grinding Rolls to (-) 75/40 microns and create slurry of 30-35 % solids concentration.\r\n<a href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Grinding-Mill.pdf">Ball Mills</a> (Grinding Mill) are also used as regrind mills in Flotation Circuits.\r\n\r\n<a title="Circular Motion" href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Circular-Motion.pdf" target="_blank"><strong>Circular Motion Screens</strong></a>\r\n\r\n<a title="Circular Motion" href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Circular-Motion.pdf" target="_blank">Circular Motion Screens</a> are used to segregate various size fractions in ore streams. Sometimes used to reduce load on crushers by removing fraction which is already smaller than required size and at other times <a title="Circular Motion" href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Circular-Motion.pdf" target="_blank">Circular Motion Screens</a> are used to recirculate oversize fractions from crushed product stream back to crushers. Possible application is in Mines before despatch to beneficiation plants and also in beneficiation plants. <a title="Circular Motion" href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Circular-Motion.pdf" target="_blank">Circular Motion Screens</a> are available in 1, 2 and 3 decks to get 2, 3 and 4 size fractions respectively. Each size fraction may be requiring different post processing.\r\n\r\n<strong>Rotary Disc Feeders</strong>\r\n\r\nRotary Disc Feeders are continuous volumetric device reclaiming dry small lumps, coarse, fine grained and powdery material from surge bins and hoppers to feed subsequent equipment. Rotary Disc Feeders can be used in chemical conditioning slurry tanks for dosing reagents.\r\n\r\n<a title="Linear Motion Screen" href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Linear-Motion-Screen1.pdf" target="_blank"><strong>Linear Motion Screens</strong></a>\r\n\r\n<a title="Linear Motion Screen" href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Linear-Motion-Screen1.pdf" target="_blank">Linear Motion Screens</a> are used for similar applications but in more demanding situations, e.g.-\r\nWhere the height is limited by surrounding facilities,\r\nFor the screening of small and short fractions\r\nWhere required throughput is high.\r\n\r\n<strong><a href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/High-Particle-Acceleration-HPA-Screen.pdf" target="_blank">High Particle Acceleration Screens</a></strong>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/High-Particle-Acceleration-HPA-Screen.pdf" target="_blank">High Particle Acceleration Screens</a> are ideally suited for screening applications for for higher level of moisture and fine grain size materials (1 mm to 10 mm) with screening capacities up to 250 metric TPH. The Inner frame is agitated by means of eccentric shaft drive. The vibration is passed on to the Outer frame via thrust rubbers.\r\nScreening mats between the inner and outer frame are clamped and flexed by the two vibrating frames. The relative movement of both screening frames creates a “trampoline effect” in the screen mats to create-\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>High acceleration up to 50g in screen mats.</li>\r\n	<li>Loosening-up and de-agglomeration of the product.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Banana Screens</strong>\r\n\r\nBanana Screens are multi-slope vibrating screens, come in single/ two/ three deck configurations and are used in place of Circular Motion Screens when higher capacities (above 400 tph) are to be processed. The angle of deck decreases from feed end to discharge end.\r\n\r\n<strong>Grizzly Screens</strong>\r\n\r\nGrizzly Screens<strong> </strong>are used in primary crushing operation as scalping screen in downstream of the Primary Ore Crusher to separate undersized and oversized ore. Typical separation is at 80 mm. Grizzly Screens are also used as Feeders to reclaim ore from Hoppers/Bins.\r\n\r\n<strong>Reciprocating Feeders</strong>\r\n\r\nReciprocating Feeders are built for high capacity reclamation from surge bins, bunker and hoppers and also as feeding equipment. A wide range of sizes is available in MSEL offerings. Heavy Duty versions with larger drives and heavier pans can be selected for coarse ores and normal versions for fine ores\r\n\r\n<strong><a href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Slurry-Pumps.pdf" target="_blank">Slurry Pumps</a></strong>\r\n\r\nIn Beneficiation plants usually the process involves transporting of Ore Slurry (suspension of Crushed/ Ground Ore in Water) between various stages. This is done by use of <a title="Slurry Pumps" href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Slurry-Pumps.pdf" target="_blank">Slurry Pumps</a>. MSEL has a vast range of Horizontal and Vertical Centrifugal Pumps catering to <a href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Slurry-Pumps.pdf" target="_blank">Slurry Pumps</a> requirements.\r\n\r\n<strong><a href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Thickener.pdf" target="_blank">Thickeners</a></strong>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Thickener.pdf" target="_blank">Thickeners</a> are used to concentrate Ore Slurry (30-35% Solids) from various stages of flotation to about 60- 70 % Solids. Overflow product is mostly water and is recycled into circuit whereas the underflow is taken for filtration (in case of Concentrate Thickeners) or to tailings as reject disposal.\r\n\r\n<strong><a href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Flotation-CELL.pdf" target="_blank">Flotation Cells</a></strong>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Flotation-CELL.pdf" target="_blank">Flotation Cells</a> are used for removal of specific impurities ore separation of different metallic particles from multi-metal ore slurries. Tests determine the size and configuration of the Flotation Cell Banks.\r\n\r\n<strong>Filter Press</strong>\r\n\r\nWe offer MSEL-Choquenet Filter Press for dewatering of concentrate or tailing in Beneficiation Circuits.', 'ZINC, LEAD, COPPER & GOLD', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '611-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-09-14 12:54:34', '2015-09-14 12:54:34', '', 611, 'http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/611-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1640, 2, '2015-09-14 12:59:13', '2015-09-14 12:59:13', '<a title="Jaw Crusher" href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Jaw-Crusher.pdf" target="_blank"><strong>Jaw Crushers</strong></a>\r\n\r\n<a title="Jaw Crusher" href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Jaw-Crusher.pdf" target="_blank">Jaw Crushers</a> are used as primary crushers in Bauxite Plants and also for spent anode butts.\r\n\r\n<a title="Apron Feeder" href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Apron-Feeder.pdf" target="_blank"><strong>Apron Feeders</strong></a>\r\n\r\n<a title="Apron Feeder" href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Apron-Feeder.pdf" target="_blank">Apron Feeders</a><strong> </strong>are extensively used to reclaim ROM/ Large Size ores from Dump Hoppers for primary crushing at mine end Ore Handling.\r\n\r\n<strong>Apron Conveyors</strong>\r\n\r\nApron Conveyors are used for conveying spent Anode Butts for recycling in Anode Paste Plants and are quite similar to Apron feeders in many respects, however Apron Conveyors may be of curved alignment and long lengths (say up to 100 M).\r\n\r\n<a title="Double Roll Crusher" href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Double-Roll-Crusher.pdf" target="_blank"><strong>Toothed Double Roll Crushers</strong></a>\r\n\r\n<a title="Double Roll Crusher" href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Double-Roll-Crusher.pdf" target="_blank">Toothed Double Roll Crushers</a> are used in crushing spent anodes in Anode Paste Plants of Aluminium Smelters.\r\n\r\n<strong>Conveyor Components</strong>\r\n\r\nMSEL product range includes all types of drive and non-drive pulleys, and idlers.\r\n\r\n<strong>Motorised Trippers</strong>\r\n\r\nBasically Motorised Trippers<strong> </strong>are rail mounted conveyor discharging equipment to uniformly distribute the conveyed Ore over a large Bin or Ground Storage stockpile.\r\n\r\n<strong>Grizzly Screens/ Feeders</strong>\r\n\r\nGrizzly Screens/ Feeder<strong>s</strong> are used in primary crushing operation in Bauxite Mining as scalping screen of the Primary Ore Crusher to separate undersized and oversized ore. Typical separation is at 80 mm. Grizzly Screens/ Feeder are also used as Feeders to reclaim ore from Hoppers/Bins.\r\n\r\n<strong>Rotary Disc Feeders</strong>\r\n\r\nRotary Disc Feeders are continuous volumetric device reclaiming dry small lumps, coarse, fine grained and powdery material e.g. coke breeze, ground bauxite, alumina etc. from surge bins and hoppers to feed subsequent equipment.\r\n\r\n<a title="Circular Motion" href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Circular-Motion.pdf" target="_blank"><strong>Circular Motion Screens</strong></a>\r\n\r\n<a title="Circular Motion" href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Circular-Motion.pdf" target="_blank">Circular Motion Screens</a> are used to segregate various size fractions in ore streams. Sometimes used to reduce load on crushers by removing fraction which is already smaller than required size at other times <a title="Circular Motion" href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Circular-Motion.pdf" target="_blank">Circular Motion Screens</a> are used to recirculate oversize fractions from crushed product stream back to crushers. Possible application is in Mines before despatch to beneficiation plants as also in beneficiation plants. <a title="Circular Motion" href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Circular-Motion.pdf" target="_blank">Circular Motion Screens</a> are available in 1, 2 and 3 decks to get 2, 3 and 4 size fractions respectively. Each size fraction may be requiring different post processing.\r\n\r\n<a title="Linear Motion Screen" href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Linear-Motion-Screen1.pdf" target="_blank"><strong>Linear Motion Screens</strong></a>\r\n\r\n<a title="Linear Motion Screen" href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Linear-Motion-Screen1.pdf" target="_blank">Linear Motion Screens</a> are used for similar applications but in more demanding situations, e.g.-\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Where the height is limited by surrounding facilities,</li>\r\n	<li>For the screening of small and short fractions</li>\r\n	<li>Where required throughput is high.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<a title="High Particle Acceleration HPA Screen" href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/High-Particle-Acceleration-HPA-Screen.pdf" target="_blank"><strong>High Particle Acceleration Screens</strong></a>\r\n\r\nAlso known as Flip Flo Screen, <a title="High Particle Acceleration HPA Screen" href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/High-Particle-Acceleration-HPA-Screen.pdf" target="_blank">High Particle Acceleration Screens</a> are ideally suited for screening applications for fine grain size materials (3 mm to 10 mm) with high moisture and screening capacities up to 250 metric TPH. The outer frame is agitated by means of eccentric shaft drive. The vibration is passed on to the inner frame via flexible thrust plates.\r\n\r\nScreening mats between the inner and outer frame are clamped and flexed by the two vibrating frames. The relative movement of both screening frames creates a “trampoline effect” in the screen mats to create-\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>High acceleration up to 50g in screen mats.</li>\r\n	<li>Loosening-up and de-agglomeration of the product.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Banana Screens</strong>\r\n\r\nBanana Screens are multi-slope vibrating screens, come in single/ two/ three deck configurations and are used in place of Circular Motion Screens when higher capacities (above 400 tph) are to be processed. The angle of deck decreases from feed end to discharge end.\r\n\r\n<strong>Cone Crushers</strong>\r\n\r\nMSEL has agency agreements with reputed manufacturers to sell Cone Crushers<strong> </strong>equipment, which are required as Secondary (-150/ 75 mm) and Tertiary Crushers (-30/ 10 mm) in Bauxite Crushing for Alumina production.\r\n\r\n<strong>Reciprocating Feeders</strong>\r\n\r\nReciprocating Feeders are built for high capacity reclamation from surge bins, bunker and hoppers and also as feeding equipment. A wide range of sizes is available in MSEL offerings. Heavy Duty versions with larger drives and heavier pans can be selected for coarse ores and normal versions for fine ores\r\n\r\n<strong>Bucket Elevators</strong>\r\n\r\nBucket Elevators<strong> </strong>are used for vertical transport of powdery, small grained bulk materials e.g. raw meal, cement, sand, grits etc. They are used in filling tall bauxite and alumina silos.\r\n\r\n<a title="Slurry Pumps" href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Slurry-Pumps.pdf" target="_blank"><strong>Slurry Pumps</strong></a>\r\n\r\nIn Beneficiation plants usually the process involves transporting of Ore Slurry (suspension of Crushed/ Ground Ore in Water) between various stages. This is done by use of Slurry Pumps. MSEL has a vast range of Horizontal and Vertical Centrifugal Pumps catering to <a title="Slurry Pumps" href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Slurry-Pumps.pdf" target="_blank">Slurry Pumps</a> requirements.\r\n\r\n<a title="Grinding Mill" href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Grinding-Mill.pdf" target="_blank"><strong>Rod Mills (Grinding Mill)</strong></a>\r\n\r\nFinal crushed ore from tertiary crushers is ground to (-) 1 mm by rod mills. MSEL has a large range of rod mills to suit most ore characteristics and product requirements.\r\n\r\n<a title="Grinding Mill" href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Grinding-Mill.pdf" target="_blank"><strong>Ball Mills (Grinding Mill)</strong></a>\r\n\r\n<a title="Grinding Mill" href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Grinding-Mill.pdf" target="_blank">Ball Mills (Grinding Mill)</a> are used for size reduction to microns and form part of grinding circuit to get the final product for calcining or Alumina refining Process. <a title="Grinding Mill" href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Grinding-Mill.pdf" target="_blank">Ball Mills (Grinding Mill)</a> are also used in Coke Grinding for Carbon Paste preparation in Aluminium Smelters.\r\n\r\n<a title="Thickener" href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Thickener.pdf" target="_blank"><strong>Thickeners</strong></a>\r\n\r\n<a title="Thickener" href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Thickener.pdf" target="_blank">Thickeners</a> are used to concentrate alumina Slurry (30-35% Solids) from refinery to about 60- 70 % Solids. Overflow product is mostly water and is recycled into circuit whereas the underflow is taken for evaporation circuit or to tailings as reject disposal.\r\n\r\n<strong>Flotation</strong>\r\n\r\nWe can offer the Beneficiation/Up gradation solution for the Bauxite ore through flotation as part of total solution for this plant which will include Crushing, Grinding, Flotation, thickening, dewatering (Filtration), slurry pumping and system integration and plant design.', 'ALUMINIUM & BAUXITE', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '615-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-09-14 12:59:13', '2015-09-14 12:59:13', '', 615, 'http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/615-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1641, 2, '2015-09-14 13:03:09', '2015-09-14 13:03:09', '<a title="Jaw Crusher" href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Jaw-Crusher.pdf" target="_blank"><strong>Jaw Crushers</strong></a>\r\n\r\n<a title="Jaw Crusher" href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Jaw-Crusher.pdf" target="_blank">Jaw Crushers</a> are used as primary/secondary crushers in Uranium Ore Mining.\r\n\r\n<a title="Apron Feeder" href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Apron-Feeder.pdf" target="_blank"><strong>Apron Feeders</strong></a>\r\n\r\n<a title="Apron Feeder" href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Apron-Feeder.pdf" target="_blank">Apron Feeders</a> are extensively used to reclaim ROM/ Large Size ores from Dump Hoppers for primary crushing at mine end Ore Handling.\r\n\r\n<strong>Roll Crushers</strong>\r\n\r\nCorrugated <a title="Double Roll Crusher" href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Double-Roll-Crusher.pdf" target="_blank">Double Roll Crushers</a> are used as secondary crushers in Uranium Ore plants to crush (-) 25 mm size. <a title="Smooth Double Roll Crusher" href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Smooth-Roll-Crusher.pdf" target="_blank">Smooth Double Roll Crushers </a>can be used for crushing normally up to (-) 5mm.\r\n\r\n<strong>Cone Crushers</strong>\r\n\r\nMSEL has agency agreements with reputed manufacturers to sell Cone Crushers equipment, which are required in secondary &amp;Tertiary Crushing of Ore for subsequent grinding to even smaller sizes.\r\n\r\n<strong>Conveyor Components</strong>\r\n\r\nMSEL product range includes all types of drive and non-drive pulleys, and idlers.\r\n\r\n<strong>Reciprocating Feeders</strong>\r\n\r\nReciprocating Feeder<strong> </strong>are built for high capacity reclamation from surge bins, bunker and hoppers and also as feeding equipment. A wide range of sizes is available in MSEL offerings. Heavy Duty versions with larger drives and heavier pans can be selected for coarse ores and normal versions for fine ores.\r\n\r\n<strong>Motorised Trippers</strong>\r\n\r\nBasically Motorised Trippers are rail mounted conveyor discharging equipment to uniformly distribute the conveyed Ore over a large Bin or Ground Storage stockpile.\r\n\r\n<strong>Grizzly Screens/ Vibrating Feeders</strong>\r\n\r\nGrizzly Screens/ Vibrating Feeders<strong> </strong>are used in primary crusher operation in Uranium Mining as scalping screen downstream of the Primary Ore Crusher to separate undersized and oversized ore. Typical separation is at 80 mm. However other opening sizes are also used depending upon feed analysis, product size etc. Vibrating feeders are also used as Feeders to reclaim ore from Hoppers/Bins or feeding to crushers/screens.\r\n\r\n<a title="Circular Motion" href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Circular-Motion.pdf" target="_blank"><strong>Circular Motion Screens</strong></a>\r\n\r\n<a title="Circular Motion" href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Circular-Motion.pdf" target="_blank">Circular Motion Screens</a> are used to segregate various size fractions in various mineral streams. Sometimes <a title="Circular Motion" href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Circular-Motion.pdf" target="_blank">Circular Motion Screens</a> are used to reduce load on crushers by removing fraction which is already smaller than required size and sometimes <a title="Circular Motion" href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Circular-Motion.pdf" target="_blank">Circular Motion Screens</a> are used to recirculate oversize fractions from crushed product stream back to crushers. Possible application is in Mines before despatch to power plants. <a title="Circular Motion" href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Circular-Motion.pdf" target="_blank">Circular Motion Screens</a> are available in 1, 2 and 3 decks to get 2, 3 and 4 size fractions respectively. Each size fraction may be requiring different post processing.\r\n\r\n<strong>Rotary Disc Feeders</strong>\r\n\r\nRotary Disc Feeders<strong> </strong>are continuous volumetric device reclaiming dry small lumps, coarse, fine grained and powdery material from surge bins and hoppers to feed subsequent equipment. Rotary Disc Feeders can be used in chemical conditioning slurry tanks for dosing reagents.\r\n\r\n<a title="Linear Motion Screen" href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Linear-Motion-Screen1.pdf" target="_blank"><strong>Linear Motion Screens</strong></a>\r\n\r\n<a title="Linear Motion Screen" href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Linear-Motion-Screen1.pdf" target="_blank">Linear Motion Screens</a> are used for similar applications but in more demanding situations, e.g.-\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Where the height is limited by surrounding facilities,</li>\r\n	<li>For the screening of small and short fractions</li>\r\n	<li>Where required throughput is high.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<a title="High Particle Acceleration HPA Screen" href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/High-Particle-Acceleration-HPA-Screen.pdf" target="_blank"><strong>High Particle Acceleration Screens</strong></a>\r\n\r\n<a title="High Particle Acceleration HPA Screen" href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/High-Particle-Acceleration-HPA-Screen.pdf" target="_blank">High Particle Acceleration Screens</a><strong> </strong>are ideally suited for heavy and very heavy screening applications for higher level of moisture and fine grain size materials (3 mm to 10 mm) with screening capacities up to 250 metric TPH. The Inner frame is agitated by means of eccentric shaft drive. The vibration is passed on to the Outer frame via flexible thrust plates.\r\nScreening mats between the inner and outer frame are clamped and flexed by the two vibrating frames. The relative movement of both screening frames creates a “trampoline effect” in the screen mats to create-\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>High acceleration up to 50g in screen mats.</li>\r\n	<li>Loosening-up and de-agglomeration of the product.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Banana Screens</strong>\r\n\r\nBanana Screens are multi-slope vibrating screens, come in single/ two/ three deck configurations and are used in place of Circular Motion Screens when higher capacities (above 400 tph) are to be processed. The angle of deck decreases from feed end to discharge end.\r\n\r\n<a title="Slurry Pumps" href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Slurry-Pumps.pdf" target="_blank"><strong>Slurry Pumps</strong></a>\r\n\r\nIn Beneficiation plants usually the process involves transporting of Ore Slurry (suspension of Crushed/ Ground Ore in Water) between various stages. This is done by use of Slurry Pumps. MSEL has a vast range of Horizontal and Vertical Centrifugal Pumps catering to <a title="Slurry Pumps" href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Slurry-Pumps.pdf" target="_blank">Slurry Pumps</a> requirements.\r\n\r\n<a title="Grinding Mill" href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Grinding-Mill.pdf" target="_blank"><strong>Rod Mills (Grinding Mill)</strong></a>\r\n\r\nFinal crushed ore from tertiary crushers is ground to (-) 1 mm by rod mills. MSEL has a large range of rod mills to suit most ore characteristics and product requirements.\r\n\r\n<a title="Grinding Mill" href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Grinding-Mill.pdf" target="_blank"><strong>Ball Mills (Grinding Mill)</strong></a>\r\n\r\n<a title="Grinding Mill" href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Grinding-Mill.pdf" target="_blank">Ball Mills (Grinding Mill)</a> are used for size reduction to microns and form part of grinding circuit to get the final product for downstream Uranium Ore beneficiation by leaching.\r\n\r\n<a title="Thickener" href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Thickener.pdf" target="_blank"><strong>Thickeners</strong></a>\r\n\r\n<a title="Thickener" href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Thickener.pdf" target="_blank">Thickeners</a><strong> </strong>are used to concentrate Uranium Slurry (30-35% Solids) from refinery to about 60- 70 % Solids. Overflow product is mostly water and is recycled into grinding circuit whereas the underflow is taken for leaching circuit or to tailings as reject disposal.', 'URANIUM', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '617-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-09-14 13:03:09', '2015-09-14 13:03:09', '', 617, 'http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/617-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1642, 2, '2015-09-14 13:08:57', '2015-09-14 13:08:57', '<a title="Apron Feeder" href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Apron-Feeder.pdf" target="_blank"><strong>Apron Feeders</strong> </a>\r\n\r\n<a title="Apron Feeder" href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Apron-Feeder.pdf" target="_blank">Apron Feeders</a> are extensively used to reclaim ROM/ Large Size ores from Dump Hoppers for primary crushing at mine end Ore Handling.\r\n\r\n<a title="Jaw Crusher" href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Jaw-Crusher.pdf" target="_blank"><strong>Jaw Crushers</strong></a>\r\n\r\n<a title="Jaw Crusher" href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Jaw-Crusher.pdf" target="_blank">Jaw Crushers</a><strong> </strong>are used as primary crushers in Rock Phosphate Mining.\r\n\r\n<strong>Roll Crushers</strong>\r\n\r\nCorrugated <a title="Double Roll Crusher" href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Double-Roll-Crusher.pdf" target="_blank">Double Roll Crushers</a> are used as secondary crushers in Rock Phosphate plants to crush (-) 25 mm size. <a title="Smooth Double Roll Crusher" href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Smooth-Roll-Crusher.pdf" target="_blank">Smooth Double Roll Crushers</a> can be used for crushing up to (-) 5mm.\r\n\r\n<strong>Cone Crushers</strong>\r\n\r\nMSEL has agency agreements with reputed manufacturers to sell Cone Crushers equipment, which are required in tertiary crushing (-30/10 mm) of Rock Phosphate for subsequent grinding to even smaller sizes.\r\n\r\n<a title="Chain Mill" href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Dual-Chain-Mill.pdf" target="_blank"><strong>Chain Mills</strong></a>\r\n\r\n<a title="Chain Mill" href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Dual-Chain-Mill.pdf" target="_blank">Chain Mills</a><strong> </strong>are special size reduction equipment in Fertiliser segment for reducing (-) 75 mm feed to (-) 6 mm lumps.\r\n\r\n<strong>Conveyor Components</strong>\r\n\r\nMSEL product range includes all types of drive and non-drive pulleys and idlers.\r\n\r\n<strong>Reciprocating Feeders</strong>\r\n\r\nReciprocating Feeders are built for high capacity reclamation from surge bins, bunker and hoppers and also as feeding equipment. A wide range of sizes is available in MSEL offerings. Heavy Duty versions with larger drives and heavier pans can be selected for coarse ores and normal versions for fine ores.\r\n\r\n<strong>Motorised Trippers</strong>\r\n\r\nBasically Motorised Trippers are rail mounted conveyor discharging equipment to uniformly distribute the conveyed Ore over a large Bin or Ground Storage stockpile.\r\n\r\n<strong>Grizzly Screens/ Feeders</strong>\r\n\r\nGrizzly Screens/ Feeders are used in primary crushing operation in Rock Phosphate Mining as scalping screen of the Primary Ore Crusher to separate undersized and oversized ore. Typical separation is at 80 mm. Grizzly Screens/ Feeders<strong> </strong>are also used as Feeders to reclaim ore from Hoppers/Bins.\r\n\r\n<a title="Circular Motion" href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Circular-Motion.pdf" target="_blank"><strong>Circular Motion Screens</strong></a>\r\n\r\n<a title="Circular Motion" href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Circular-Motion.pdf" target="_blank">Circular Motion Screens</a> are used to segregate various size fractions in various mineral streams. Sometimes <a title="Circular Motion" href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Circular-Motion.pdf" target="_blank">Circular Motion Screens</a> are used to reduce load on crushers by removing fraction which is already smaller than required size and sometimes <a title="Circular Motion" href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Circular-Motion.pdf" target="_blank">Circular Motion Screens</a> are used to recirculate oversize fractions from crushed product stream back to crushers. Possible application is in Mines before despatch to power plants. <a title="Circular Motion" href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Circular-Motion.pdf" target="_blank">Circular Motion Screens</a> are available in 1, 2 and 3 decks to get 2, 3 and 4 size fractions respectively. Each size fraction may be requiring different post processing.\r\n\r\n<a title="High Particle Acceleration HPA Screen" href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/High-Particle-Acceleration-HPA-Screen.pdf" target="_blank"><strong>High Particle Acceleration Screens</strong></a>\r\n\r\n<a title="High Particle Acceleration HPA Screen" href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/High-Particle-Acceleration-HPA-Screen.pdf" target="_blank">High Particle Acceleration Screens</a> are ideally suited for screening applications for higher level of moisture and fine grain size materials (3 mm to 10 mm) with screening capacities up to 250 metric TPH. In Iron Ore &amp; Steel industry <a title="High Particle Acceleration HPA Screen" href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/High-Particle-Acceleration-HPA-Screen.pdf" target="_blank">High Particle Acceleration Screens</a><strong> </strong>are used for fine screening in Flux Crushing &amp; Screening circuits. The Inner frame is agitated by means of eccentric shaft drive. The vibration is passed on to the Outer frame via flexible thrust springs.\r\n\r\nScreening mats between the inner and outer frame are clamped and flexed by the two vibrating frames. The relative movement of both screening frames creates a “trampoline effect” in the screen mats to create-\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>High acceleration up to 50g in screen mats.</li>\r\n	<li>Loosening-up and de-agglomeration of the product.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<a title="Slurry Pumps" href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Slurry-Pumps.pdf" target="_blank"><strong>Slurry Pumps</strong></a>\r\n\r\nIn Rock Phosphate beneficiation plants usually the process involves transporting of Ore Slurry (suspension of Crushed/ Ground Ore in Water) between various stages. This is done by use of Slurry Pumps. MSEL has a vast range of Horizontal and Vertical Centrifugal Pumps catering to <a title="Slurry Pumps" href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Slurry-Pumps.pdf" target="_blank">Slurry Pumps</a><strong> </strong>requirements.\r\n\r\n<a title="Grinding Mill" href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Grinding-Mill.pdf" target="_blank"><strong>Rod Mills (Grinding Mill)</strong></a>\r\n\r\nFinal crushed ore from tertiary crushers is ground to (-) 1 mm by rod mills. MSEL has a large range of rod mills to suit most ore characteristics and product requirements.\r\n\r\n<a title="Grinding Mill" href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Grinding-Mill.pdf" target="_blank"><strong>Ball Mills (Grinding Mill)</strong></a>\r\n\r\n<a title="Grinding Mill" href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Grinding-Mill.pdf" target="_blank">Ball Mills (Grinding Mill)</a><strong> </strong>are used for size reduction to microns and form part of grinding circuit to get the final product for downstream Ore beneficiation.\r\n\r\n<a title="Flotation Cell" href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Flotation-CELL.pdf" target="_blank"><strong>Flotation Cells</strong></a>\r\n\r\n<a title="Flotation Cell" href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Flotation-CELL.pdf" target="_blank">Flotation Cells</a><strong> </strong>are used for Silica removal as underflow in first stage of flotation, whereas Phosphates and Carbonates are extracted as froth.\r\n\r\nIn second stage additional bank of <a title="Flotation Cell" href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Flotation-CELL.pdf" target="_blank">Flotation Cells</a> are used to remove carbonate (rejects) as froth and Phosphate Concentrates as underflow, which is then processed through cleaner flotation Cells before taking for thickener concentration and filtration.\r\n\r\n<strong>Banana Screens</strong>\r\n\r\nBanana Screens<strong> </strong>are multi-slope vibrating screens, come in single/ two deck configurations and are used in place of Circular Motion Screens when higher capacities (above 400 tph) are to be processed. The angle of deck decreases from feed end to discharge end.\r\n\r\n<a title="Thickener" href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Thickener.pdf" target="_blank"><strong>Thickeners</strong></a>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a title="Thickener" href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Thickener.pdf" target="_blank">Thickeners</a><strong> </strong>are used to concentrate silica Slurry (30-35% Solids) underflow from first flotation stage to about 60- 70 % Solids before sending Thickener underflow to tailings disposal as rejects. Thickener Overflow product is mostly water and is recycled into grinding circuit.</li>\r\n	<li>Another set of thickeners are used to process Carbonate froth from Second stage flotation, recycling the thickener overflow as Process water and sending thickener underflow as tailings for reject disposal.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Vibrating Tube Mills</strong>\r\n\r\nVibrating Tube Mills are for continuous or batch grinding of materials to a very fine end product. Two vibrating/ grinding cylinders are placed either directly above the other or inclined at 30 degrees to perpendicular. Located between the two tubes, an eccentrically supported weight is driven to produce a small circular vibration. The tubes are charged with ball or rod media to aid in the grinding action (attrition) from the constant impulses. Material is ground as it travels from the input end of the tube to the outlet end.\r\n\r\nVibrating Tube Mills have a very small size and low energy consumption compared to other mill types and are used in manufacture of paints and varnishes where ultra- fines (of the order 10-20 microns) are required. Output is restricted to 5-10 tph. We offer Vibrating Tube Mills<strong> </strong>from our Baroda plant.', 'ROCK PHOSPHATE', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '621-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-09-14 13:08:57', '2015-09-14 13:08:57', '', 621, 'http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/621-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1643, 2, '2015-09-14 13:12:33', '2015-09-14 13:12:33', 'MSEL manufacture cement plant equipment such as crushers, ball mills, material handling equipment, feeders, wagon tipplers, bucket wheel stacker cum Reclaimers. They are listed below-\r\n\r\n<a title="Jaw Crusher" href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Jaw-Crusher.pdf" target="_blank"><strong>Jaw Crushers</strong></a>\r\n\r\n<a title="Jaw Crusher" href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Jaw-Crusher.pdf" target="_blank">Jaw Crushers</a> are used as alternatives to Gyratory Crushers as primary crushers for crushing limestone when the throughput needed is less than 500-600 metric TPH. For hard ores Double Toggle Jaw Crushers and for softer ores Single Toggle Jaw Crushers are customary,\r\n\r\n<a title="Reversible Hammer Mill" href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Reversible-Hammer-Mill.pdf" target="_blank"><strong>Hammer Mills (Reversible Hammer Mill)</strong></a>\r\n\r\nReversible Hammer Mills, Open Bottom or With Grate bar type are used as secondary crushing of Limestone and Clinker.\r\n\r\n<a title="Heavy Duty Impactor" href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Heavy-Duty-Impactor.pdf" target="_blank"><strong>Heavy Duty Impactors</strong></a>\r\n\r\nFor higher capacities and crushing to (-) 20 mm, impactors are used for crushing Clinker.\r\n\r\n<strong>Bucket Elevators</strong>\r\n\r\nBucket Elevators<strong> </strong>are used for vertical transport of powdery, small grained bulk materials e.g. raw meal, cement, bauxite, limestone, clinker, fly-ash etc.\r\n\r\n<strong>Rotary Disc Feeders</strong>\r\n\r\nRotary Disc Feeders<strong> </strong>are continuous volumetric device reclaiming dry small lumps, coarse, fine grained and powdery material from surge bins and hoppers to feed subsequent equipment. In cement Rotary Disc Feeders can be used for dosing additives.\r\n\r\n<a title="Apron Feeder" href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Apron-Feeder.pdf" target="_blank"><strong>Apron Feeders</strong></a>\r\n\r\n<a title="Apron Feeder" href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Apron-Feeder.pdf" target="_blank">Apron Feeders</a><strong> </strong>are extensively used to reclaim ROM/ Large Size Limestone from Dump Hoppers for primary crushing.\r\n\r\n<strong>Conveyor Components</strong>\r\n\r\nMSEL product range includes all types of drive and non-drive pulleys, and idlers.\r\n\r\n<strong>Motorised Trippers</strong>\r\n\r\nBasically Motorised Trippers<strong> </strong>are rail mounted conveyor discharging equipment to uniformly distribute the conveyed Ore over a large Bin or Ground Storage stockpile.\r\n\r\n<strong><a title="Rotary Scrubber" href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Rotary-Scrubber.pdf" target="_blank">Drum Scrubbers</a> (Rotary Scrubber)</strong>\r\n\r\n<a title="Rotary Scrubber" href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Rotary-Scrubber.pdf" target="_blank">Drum Scrubbers</a> (Rotary Scrubber) are used to clean clayey/siliceous coatings from ore lumps as the first stage of raw material preparation.\r\n\r\n<a title="Circular Motion" href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Circular-Motion.pdf" target="_blank"><strong>Circular Motion Screen</strong></a>\r\n\r\n<a title="Circular Motion" href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Circular-Motion.pdf" target="_blank">Circular Motion Screens</a> are used to segregate various size fractions in ore streams. Sometimes used to reduce load on crushers by removing fraction which is already smaller than required size at other times <a title="Circular Motion" href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Circular-Motion.pdf" target="_blank">Circular Motion Screens</a> are used to recirculate oversize fractions from crushed product stream back to crushers. Possible application is in Mines before despatch to beneficiation plants as also in beneficiation plants. <a title="Circular Motion" href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Circular-Motion.pdf" target="_blank">Circular Motion Screens</a> are available in 1, 2 and 3 decks to get 2, 3 and 4 size fractions respectively. Each size fraction may be requiring different post processing.\r\n\r\n<a title="Linear Motion Screen" href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Linear-Motion-Screen1.pdf" target="_blank"><strong>Linear Motion Screens</strong></a>\r\n\r\nLinear Motion Screens are used for similar applications but in more demanding situations, e.g.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Where the height is limited by surrounding facilities,</li>\r\n	<li>For the screening of small and short fractions</li>\r\n	<li>Where required throughput is high.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<a title="High Particle Acceleration HPA Screen" href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/High-Particle-Acceleration-HPA-Screen.pdf" target="_blank"><strong>High Particle Acceleration Screens</strong></a>\r\n\r\n<a title="High Particle Acceleration HPA Screen" href="http://mcnallysayaji.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/High-Particle-Acceleration-HPA-Screen.pdf" target="_blank">High Particle Acceleration Screens</a> are ideally suited for screening applications for fine grain size materials (1 mm to 10 mm) with screening capacities up to 250 metric TPH. The base frame is agitated by means of eccentric shaft drive. The vibration is passed on to the dynamic frame via thrust rubbers.\r\nScreening mats between the inner and outer frame are clamped and flexed by the two vibrating frames. The relative movement of both screening frames creates a “trampoline effect” in the screen mats to create\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>High acceleration up to 50g in screen mats.</li>\r\n	<li>Loosening-up and de-agglomeration of the product.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Grizzly Screens</strong>\r\n\r\nGrizzly Screens are used in primary crushing circuit as scalping screen downstream of the Primary Ore Crusher to separate undersized and oversized ore. Typical separation is at 80 mm. Grizzly Screens are also used as Feeders to reclaim ore from Hoppers/Bins.\r\n\r\n<strong>Flotation Cells</strong>\r\n\r\nWe can offer Flotation cells for the lime ore Beneficiation or silica removal.\r\n\r\nSlurry Pump\r\n\r\nSlurry Pump for capacity of 2500M3/Hr is available in our regular product range for use in Lime ore beneficiation and silica removal.\r\n\r\nThickener\r\n\r\nFor the thickening of the limestone slurry/ tailing etc. we can offer proven thickening solution customised for the process requirement.\r\n\r\nLime Stone Beneficiation Plant\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>We can offer the total limestone scrubbing plant with engineering for the small up gradation and removal of soil etc.</li>\r\n	<li>For the Low grade lime stone we can give the flotation Plant with all the equipment and engineering.</li>\r\n</ol>', 'CEMENT', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '633-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-09-14 13:12:33', '2015-09-14 13:12:33', '', 633, 'http://dev1.businessprodemo.com/Mcnallybharat/php/633-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
